base_text: The Chapel of Virgin Mary is a small place of Christian worship dedicated specifically to the Virgin Mary, the mother of Jesus Christ. These chapels are typically contained within a larger church or cathedral. The term 'chapel' comes from the French word 'chapele' which signifies a place of worship smaller than a church. The 'Virgin Mary' part of the term refers to Mary as designated in the New Testament of the Bible, who conceived Jesus through a miraculous, non-physical conception.  The dedicating of a chapel to the Virgin Mary shows special reverence and respect for her role in Christianity. It is common in Roman Catholic, Anglican, and Orthodox Christian traditions. These chapels usually contain an altar, religious images or statues of Mary, and possibly relics associated with her. In these chapels, special prayers, sermons or services dedicated to Mary might be conducted. They may also serve as places of reflection and prayer for worshippers seeking intercession from the Virgin Mary. Ultimately, the Chapel of Virgin Mary is a significant spiritual and religious symbol in Christianity.
sumy: These chapels usually contain an altar, religious images or statues of Mary, and possibly relics associated with her.

base_text: Leon Panetta is a renowned American politician and lawyer. He was born on June 28, 1938, in California. He is best known for his service within the United States government, where he held several key leadership positions. Panetta served as the Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) from 2009 to 2011 under President Barack Obama. Subsequently, from 2011 to 2013, he took up the role of Secretary of Defense, again during the Obama administration. Prior to these roles, Panetta was the White House Chief of Staff for President Bill Clinton from 1994 to 1997. In his early political career, he was a member of the U.S. House of Representatives from California's 16th district. He is also the co-founder of the Panetta Institute for Public Policy. His years of public service have influenced significant policy decisions and have significantly impacted U.S. government operations. His seasoned experience in politics and administration render his name noteworthy in political discussions.
sumy: Leon Panetta is a renowned American politician and lawyer.

base_text: The term Ghumdan Palace refers to an ancient fort based in the city of Sanaa in Yemen. Built in pre-Islamic times, Ghumdan Palace is one of the most well-known historical sites in the country. It is known for its unique architectural design, height, and antiquity. The palace once stood as a 20-story building, making it one of the oldest skyscrapers in the world. It was constructed with large square stone blocks and ornate carved windows. Some believe it to be the legendary "Palace of Bilqis", also known as the Palace of the Queen of Sheba. However, the palace no longer exists in its full form; it was destroyed and remains in ruins. Despite this, its legendary status has made it a focal point of Yemeni cultural heritage. Ghumdan Palace is also referred to in several ancient texts and poetry. Its historical significance and grandeur make it a symbol of ancient Yemeni civilization.
sumy: Despite this, its legendary status has made it a focal point of Yemeni cultural heritage.

base_text: Asmongold, whose real name is Zack, is a widely recognized and popular video game streamer from the United States. He is most well-known for his live streams on the platform Twitch, where he primarily plays the game "World of Warcraft". Asmongold has played World of Warcraft since it was released and this dedication is reflected in his impressive knowledge of the game. Asmongold is known for his engaging personality and humor, often providing commentary and insights while playing. Over the years, he has managed to amass a large following due to his entertaining style and skill in the game. Besides gaming, Asmongold also engages in discussions about video game culture and the industry as a whole. He is often cited as a major influencer within the gaming community. His popularity has grown significantly over time, turning his passion for video games into a viable career. Although he is particularly known for his World of Warcraft streams, Asmongold occasionally diversifies his content by playing other games on stream. His content often centers around games but can stray into other lifestyle and entertainment topics.
sumy: Besides gaming, Asmongold also engages in discussions about video game culture and the industry as a whole.

base_text: John Meurig Thomas is a renowned British scientist who made significant contributions to the field of materials science and catalysis. He was born in 1932 in Wales. Thomas is most known for his work on the concept and procedures of single-site heterogeneous catalysis. His work has been instrumental in advancing our understanding of solid-state chemistry and the properties of materials on a molecular level. He has served at top universities, including University College of Wales where he was a professor and the University of Cambridge as the head of the department. He's written numerous scientific papers and authored several books. In 1991, he was knighted by Queen Elizabeth II for his service to chemistry and education. He has also received the prestigious Royal Medal from the Royal Society in 2006 for his innovative work in catalysis. His research has been applied in several industries such as pharmaceuticals, petrochemicals, and environmental science. Hence, the term John Meurig Thomas is often mentioned in connection with these fields of study and research.
sumy: John Meurig Thomas is a renowned British scientist who made significant contributions to the field of materials science and catalysis.

base_text: Aurangzeb, also known as Alamgir, was a Mughal emperor who reigned from 1658 to 1707 over what is now India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, and Afghanistan. He was the third son and last of the six notable Mughal emperors. He was a ruthless leader, often remembered for his strict adherence to Islam and attempts to enforce Islamic law across the region. This led to a lot of religious tension and conflict during his reign. Aurangzeb expanded the Mughal Empire to its greatest extent, but his oppressive regime led to its downfall. He seized the throne from his father, Shah Jahan, after a brutal civil war with his brothers. Aurangzeb is often credited with the ushering in of the long period of decline of the Mughal dynasty. He is noted for his architectural achievements, such as the Badshahi Mosque in Lahore. However, his rule is also marked by countless wars, execution of his own brothers, heavy taxation, and religious intolerance. Overall, Aurangzeb had a significant impact, shaping the political and religious landscapes of South Asia.
sumy: Aurangzeb, also known as Alamgir, was a Mughal emperor who reigned from 1658 to 1707 over what is now India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, and Afghanistan.

base_text: "Bring the Noise" is a phrase that originated from a popular song by the American hip-hop group Public Enemy, released in 1987. The term has since permeated popular culture and is often used to encourage excitement, energy, and participation. It can be used in various contexts, suggesting someone to make their presence felt, or to contribute with enthusiasm and vigor. It's often heard in musical or performance settings where the aim is to create a lively and energetic atmosphere. In sports, fans are exhorted to 'bring the noise' to boost the morale of their team. However, it isn't restricted only to literal noise; it is more about making a significant contribution or impact. So, when someone says 'bring the noise', they're asking you to step up, stand out, and make some waves with whatever you're doing. It's a call to action, urging people to give their all to a particular endeavor. It's less about causing a disturbance, and more about creating momentum, enthusiasm, and influence.
sumy: "Bring the Noise" is a phrase that originated from a popular song by the American hip-hop group Public Enemy, released in 1987.

base_text: Madisar is a form of traditional saree that is worn by Brahmin women from Tamil Nadu, South India. This saree style is usually worn during special occasions, religious ceremonies, and traditional functions. The Madisar is distinct from a regular saree because it is nine yards long, compared to the usual five to six yards of a typical Indian saree. The method of tying or draping this saree is also different and more complicated than regular ones. The style of tying the Madisar originated in the Madisar region of Tamil Nadu, which is how it got its name. This attire holds significance in traditional ceremonies and is a way of preserving cultural heritage. It symbolizes respect and honor in their community. This saree style is generally worn in two parts, with the pleats positioned at the back. Usually, the Madisar is red or maroon, representing the marital status of women. Over time, modern versions of this saree have been created, and it is worn less frequently, often replaced by the more manageable five-yard saree.
sumy: This saree style is usually worn during special occasions, religious ceremonies, and traditional functions.

base_text: Surrealism is a cultural, intellectual, and artistic movement that started in the early 1920s, most notably recognized in art and literature. Influenced by the Dadaist movement, it was initiated by poet Andre Breton’s Surrealist Manifesto. The intention of Surrealism is to reconcile the conscious and unconscious realms of experience so reality is redefined on a dreamlike and imaginative plane. Surrealists aim to express the workings of the mind by using unconventional techniques and irrational imagery. In art, this manifests as bizarre and unexpected scenes and in literature, it's seen through a juxtaposition of unrelated images. The movement was a reaction against what its members saw as the destruction wrought by rationalism in the First World War. Key figures include Salvador Dalí, René Magritte, and Max Ernst. Surrealism's influence continues in pop culture, advertising, and various creative expressions. It attempts to challenge preconceived perceptions of reality, encouraging a deeper understanding of the human psyche. The adoption of Surrealism by the fashion, photography, and graphic design industries shows its pervasive influence.
sumy: The intention of Surrealism is to reconcile the conscious and unconscious realms of experience so reality is redefined on a dreamlike and imaginative plane.

base_text: The Inland Printer was a trade magazine that was first published in the United States in the late 19th century, specifically in 1883. It was heavily focused on the printing industry and its various branches, including graphic design and typography. It was renowned not just as a source of information, but also for the quality of its own design and typography. One of its main goals was to improve the standards of printed materials through promoting and highlighting the importance of good quality design and craftsmanship in the industry. Additionally, the magazine served as a crucial platform for professional networking and exchange for industry professionals, including printers, designers and publishers. Over the years, it underwent several name changes and mergers with other trade publications, finally being published as American Printer until it ceased publication in 2011 due to industry-wide challenges. Despite its closure, it is widely considered a significant contributor to the development and evolution of the printing and graphic design industries. Today, digital copies of past issues continue to serve as a valuable resource for researchers and students in the field. So, The Inland Printer was not only a magazine, but it played a pivotal role in how the printing industry evolved over the years.
sumy: Over the years, it underwent several name changes and mergers with other trade publications, finally being published as American Printer until it ceased publication in 2011 due to industry-wide challenges.

base_text: The Marin Museum of Contemporary Art, also known as MarinMOCA, is a vibrant art center located in Marin County, California. This museum is home to more than 40 working artists. It offers exhibitions that feature local, national, and international artists. The museum aims to promote and champion art and artists, ensuring contemporary art remains an accessible part of community life. Aside from showcasing art, MarinMOCA offers educational opportunities such as art classes and workshops. It also hosts regular public programs such as lectures, panels, and art talks. The museum is housed in a unique and historic building, previously a U.S. Navy Air Station. Providing local artists an affordable workspace, the museum acts like an incubator for creativity and expression. It's a well-liked destination for culture vultures who appreciate modern art. Therefore, it's not just a museum, but rather a hub for contemporary art and culture.
sumy: It offers exhibitions that feature local, national, and international artists.

base_text: Webster County Jails refer to the correctional facilities located in Webster County, in different U.S. states. The primary function of these jails is to house individuals who have allegedly violated the law within the jurisdiction of Webster County. Like other county jails, they typically hold arrestees who are waiting for court proceedings or sentences, as well as those serving short-term sentences. Some examples of Webster County Jails include the ones in states such as Iowa, Missouri, and Georgia. Larger jails may have sections or divisions for different populations, like high-risk inmates, pretrial detainees, or women. Services often provided by these jails include inmate programs for mental health, substance abuse, or vocational training. Security and order are maintained by trained correctional officers. Inmates' visitation, communication, and other rights are governed by specific regulations. The management and operation of these jails are overseen by the Webster County Sheriff's Department. All in all, Webster County Jails are an integral part of the local criminal justice system.
sumy: Some examples of Webster County Jails include the ones in states such as Iowa, Missouri, and Georgia.

base_text: Eildon Hill is a complex of three hills located near Melrose in the Scottish Borders region of Scotland. It’s known for its distinctive, triple-peaked shape that forms its unique landscape. The hills hold archaeological significance featuring remains of prehistoric forts and settlements. The largest hill, Eildon Hill North, was uniquely a significant Iron Age hill fort. According to Roman histories, it was one of the largest settlements in Scotland around 100 AD. The hills also have connections to various legends, one of them linking to the King Arthur. Furthermore, it has connections to Sir Walter Scott, who lived nearby and frequently referred to Eildon Hill in his works. The area is now popular with walkers offering trails with panoramic views at the summits. It also offers a wide variety of flora and fauna. Today, Eildon Hill forms part of a designated Area of Great Landscape Value.
sumy: The hills hold archaeological significance featuring remains of prehistoric forts and settlements.

base_text: Longchang is a county-level city located in the northeast of Sichuan Province, China. It is administered by the prefecture-level city of Neijiang. Longchang has a rich history dating back to the Han Dynasty and it's known for its historical sites. Its geography is characterized by hilly areas, with abundant natural resources. The city has an agrarian economy with prominent farming of crops such as rice, wheat and oil-producing plants. They also have a practiced animal husbandry and the city processes farm products for distribution. Besides agriculture, Longchang also has developed industries, most notably in sectors like food, textiles, chemicals, and machinery. The transport system in Longchang is well-developed with railways and highways providing connections to other parts of China. Lastly, the city is home to a variety of local traditions and festivals, which together with its historical sites, attracts many tourists every year. Longchang enjoys a subtropical climate, with four distinct seasons.
sumy: Longchang has a rich history dating back to the Han Dynasty and it's known for its historical sites.

base_text: HD Radio is a proprietary broadcasting technology developed by iBiquity Digital Corp. It is employed by AM and FM radio stations to transmit audio and data by using a digital signal embedded within a station's regular analog signal. The "HD" is not an abbreviation for high definition or hybrid digital, as commonly believed, but is simply a trademarked term. HD Radio provides superior sound quality compared to analog signals and can broadcast text information such as song titles, artist names and weather updates. It has the ability to multi-cast, which allows stations to broadcast two or more programs simultaneously. HD radio is free to listen to, you just need an HD radio receiver. In addition to improved sound quality, listeners also benefit from a wider range of programming due to multi-casting. It's worth noting, however, that HD radio signals have a shorter range than their analog counterparts. HD radio is currently being adopted by various broadcasters around the world, with a significant presence in North America.
sumy: HD Radio is a proprietary broadcasting technology developed by iBiquity Digital Corp.

base_text: Mecklenburgh Square is a famous garden square located in London, England. Named after Queen Charlotte of Mecklenburg-Strelitz, the wife of King George III, this square is a part of the historic Bloomsbury district. Constructed in the early 19th century, the square is known for its architectural beauty and its serene surroundings. The square encompasses rows of beautiful Georgian terraced houses that overlook a large central private garden. The garden is noted for its beautiful planting and it's design that reflect the popular landscape styles of the period. Notably, it was once home to several influential literary and intellectual figures including novelist Dorothy Richardson and poet and critic H.D. The University of London is adjacent to the square, providing an educational backdrop. The square also sits near other iconic landmarks such as the British Museum. Today, Mecklenburgh Square remains an important historical site that attracts tourists and locals alike. It continues to inspire, preserving its charm and elegance in the midst of the bustling city.
sumy: Constructed in the early 19th century, the square is known for its architectural beauty and its serene surroundings.

base_text: A bearded mountaineer is a type of bird that is endemic to the country of New Zealand. It gets its name from the fine plumes, or beard-like appendages hanging below its neck. This bird is very unique and is not found anywhere else in the world. The bearded mountaineer is predominantly honeyeaters and its diet consists mainly of nectar from flowers, but it also feeds on insects and spiders. This bird is attracted to a range of native and exotic flowers. They are not migratory birds and tend to stay in one area or only travel short distances. Bearded Mountaineers are known for their distinctive song and rapid flight actions. This bird has a beak curved downward to assist with nectar-related feeding. Bearded mountaineers are being threatened by habitat loss and predation. Therefore, efforts are consistently made to protect the habitat of these birds.
sumy: This bird is attracted to a range of native and exotic flowers.

base_text: Fred Wacker was an American engineer and racing driver known mainly for his contributions to the world of motor sports. He was born in Chicago, Illinois in 1918. Wacker's racing career began in the late 1940s when he purchased a Crosley HotShot, which he later modified for racing. Wacker quickly became successful in racing, winning many local and international championships. He went on to compete in the Formula One World Championship in 1953 and 1954. Apart from racing, Fred Wacker also served as the president of the family business - the Wacker Chemical Corporation before he sold the company. He also played a significant role in the creation of the Road America racetrack in Wisconsin. Wacker was inducted into the SCCA Hall of Fame for his contribution to motor sports. Sadly, he passed away on September 16, 1998. Thus, Fred Wacker made significant strides in motor sports and business during his lifetime.
sumy: Fred Wacker was an American engineer and racing driver known mainly for his contributions to the world of motor sports.

base_text: The term "Cambridgeshire Lodes" refers to a series of man-made waterways found in the eastern part of the county of Cambridgeshire in the United Kingdom. They were historically created to transport goods such as coal, wool, and livestock from one area to another. These waterways connect numerous villages and towns in the region, providing a scenic and tranquil atmosphere. They are navigable and play a significant role in leisure boating activities in Cambridgeshire. Most of these waterways were dug during the Roman era with some possibly even earlier. The name "lode" comes from an Anglo-Saxon word meaning watercourse. The Cambridgeshire Lodes are an important part of the Fens' drainage system as well. Some of the notable Lodes include Burwell Lode, Reach Lode, and Wicken Lode. Conservation efforts are ongoing to preserve these historical waterways. Today, they serve as favourite spots for walking, boating, and wildlife observation.
sumy: Most of these waterways were dug during the Roman era with some possibly even earlier.

base_text: Sarah Elmira Shelton was an important figure in U.S. literature history as she was the fiancée of the renowned author, Edgar Allan Poe. Born Sarah Elmira Royster in Richmond, Virginia, in 1810, she was romantically involved with Poe during adolescence. The two planned to marry, but their relationship was interrupted when Poe left for university. Royster went on to marry Alexander Shelton, taking his last name. After Shelton's death in 1844, Poe tried rekindling his relationship with Sarah, even leading to their eventual engagement in 1849. However, Poe passed away a few months later, and they were never married. Sarah remained in Richmond until her death in 1888. She is often associated closely with Poe's works, with scholars analyzing their relationship in the writer's texts. Sarah Elmira Shelton thus holds a significant place in the wider narrative of American Gothic literature.
sumy: The two planned to marry, but their relationship was interrupted when Poe left for university.

base_text: Ernst Hinterseer is a notable figure in the world of Alpine skiing, not a term. Born in Austria in 1932, Hinterseer rose to fame as a professional ski racer, representing his country on the international stage. He achieved significant success in his career, earning multiple titles. Among his most noteworthy achievements was a gold medal at the 1960 Winter Olympics in Squaw Valley, U.S.A., in the slalom category. In addition to this, he also won three world championship medals. Following his retirement from competitive skiing, Hinterseer made a career in ski instruction. He is also known as the father of popular Austrian singer and TV presenter, Hansi Hinterseer. Today, Ernst Hinterseer is remembered as one of the greats in skiing history, his legacy continuing through his contributions to the sport.
sumy: In addition to this, he also won three world championship medals.

base_text: Franciscans are members of a Roman Catholic religious order founded by Saint Francis of Assisi in the 13th century. They are also known as the Order of Friars Minor, and are traditionally divided into three groups: the Order of Friars Minor, Order of Saint Clare, and the Third Order of Saint Francis. Franciscans follow a lifestyle of simplicity, poverty, and humility, as demonstrated by their founder, who renounced worldly goods to devote himself to God. They live in communities, typically called friaries, and serve in various ministerial roles, including parish work, education, and missionary work. They do not necessarily live in solitude like monks but involve themselves in the world, providing service to others. This order has a strong emphasis on care for the poor and stewardship of the environment. The wearing of brown or grey robes with a cord symbolizing their vow of poverty, is one notable aspect of the Franciscans. Famous Franciscans include Saint Anthony of Padua and Saint Bonaventure, and the present Pope Francis is a Jesuit but named himself after Francis of Assisi due to his appreciation of the Franciscan values. The Franciscan order, today, continues to be a significant presence within the Catholic Church all over the world.
sumy: Franciscans follow a lifestyle of simplicity, poverty, and humility, as demonstrated by their founder, who renounced worldly goods to devote himself to God.

base_text: The term "way up high" is an English phrase often used to describe something that is in a high or elevated position. It could be used in the literal sense to describe physical altitude. For instance, objects like stars or mountains can be said to be "way up high" because of their elevation. It may also be referring to items placed at the top of a structure, like a book on a high shelf. The term can also apply metaphorically to someone achieving high social status or reaching an elevated level of success. It can further be used in a narrative or poetic context to dramatize the description of height or the notion of being a great distance from the ground. It's a very versatile phrase, found throughout literature, daily conversation, and even song lyrics. This term generally signals a significant distance or progress upwards from a starting point.
sumy: It could be used in the literal sense to describe physical altitude.

base_text: Shenyang is the capital city and a major economic hub of the northeast province of Liaoning in the People's Republic of China. This city served as the imperial capital of the Qing Dynasty for more than 200 years, creating a significant historical and cultural background. Today, it stands as a mecca for heavy industry in China, known for its automotive, aerospace, and metallurgy sectors. Shenyang is also a key transportation hub and features an extensive network of roads, railways, and a large international airport. Besides industry and transportation, it houses several renowned educational institutions and research centers. A place of cultural interest, it is home to the UNESCO World Heritage Sites of Shenyang Imperial Palace and the Eastern and Western tombs of the Qing Dynasty. The city's architecture is a mix of traditional northeastern Chinese designs and modern high-rises. It also has several public parks and gardens which illustrate the city's commitment to urban environmental concerns. Shenyang has a population of almost 8 million people. The local climate features hot, humid summers and cold, dry winters, characteristic of its East Asian location.
sumy: The city's architecture is a mix of traditional northeastern Chinese designs and modern high-rises.

base_text:
The Yamaha FZR600 is a sports motorcycle that was produced by the Japanese motorcycle manufacturer Yamaha between the years 1989 and 1999. It is a part of Yamaha's FZR series which was primarily designed for speed and performance, hence the sports bike classification. Initially, the FZR600 was considered the middleweight class in the FZR series, positioned between the FZR400 and the FZR1000. 

This model featured a liquid-cooled, four-cylinder engine with a displacement of 599cc. This powerplant allows the bike to reach impressive speeds, making it a favorite among motorcycle enthusiasts. It's notable that the FZR600 came with a "Deltabox" frame which was innovative at the time, providing improved structural rigidity and handling. This bike also utilized a unique four-into-one exhaust, improving power output and overall performance.

The Yamaha FZR600 was popular both in the market and in professional motorcycle racing, participating, and often succeeding in various sports bike championships. Since 1999, the model has been discontinued, however, it is still respected in the biking community and sought after by collectors and motorcycle enthusiasts for its unique blend of power, performance, and distinctive style.
sumy: It is a part of Yamaha's FZR series which was primarily designed for speed and performance, hence the sports bike classification.

base_text: Bankera is a digital banking platform that integrates traditional banking systems with blockchain technologies. It is designed to offer services such as payments, loans, and investments for both cryptocurrencies and fiat currencies. Bankera aims to cater to the needs of the blockchain community by providing innovative solutions that bridge the gap between these two domains of finance. It offers a high level of convenience and functionality with services such as online banking, a mobile app, payment cards and a payment gateway for merchants. Bankera emphasizes security as a critical aspect, thus ensuring safe transactions for its users. Additionally, this platform enables users to invest in various products including ETFs and crypto funds. It was established as part of SpectroCoin, a one-stop solution for Bitcoin since 2013, indicating an experienced and knowledgeable team behind the product. Through Bankera's Exchange platform, users can trade digital assets. The company aims to provide a comprehensive and decentralized banking solution on the blockchain. The ultimate goal of Bankera is to become a blockchain-based bank with a focus on providing effective, secure, and user-friendly services.
sumy: Bankera emphasizes security as a critical aspect, thus ensuring safe transactions for its users.

base_text: A biological life cycle is a series of changes in form that an organism undergoes, returning to the starting state. It comprises various stages from conception to reproduction in next generation. The concept applies to all lifeforms such as plants, animals, fungi and protists. In simpler organisms like bacteria, this cycle involves growth and division into two daughter cells in a process known as binary fission. Complex organisms like humans go through a life cycle that includes stages like birth, maturation, adulthood, and death. Plants also have a biological life cycle which often involves alternating sexual and asexual reproductive phases. Some organisms have straightforward life cycles, while others like insects and amphibians undergo dramatic transformations in a process called metamorphosis. The exact structure and duration of the life cycle can greatly vary between different species. The purpose of each biological life cycle is to ensure the survival and propagation of the species. Hence, each stage is crucial for the continuation of life on Earth.
sumy: The concept applies to all lifeforms such as plants, animals, fungi and protists.

base_text: The Swarbriggs is a term used to refer to two Irish brothers, Tommy and Jimmy Swarbrigg, who were popular musicians in the late 20th century, especially known for representing Ireland in the Eurovision Song Contest. Their music spanned various genres including pop and folk. The brother duo participated in the Eurovision Song Contest twice, in 1975 and 1977, achieving respectable positions each time. Their most successful song was "That's What Friends Are For", which secured a third-place finish for Ireland in the 1975 Eurovision Song Contest. Apart from singing, they also played different instruments. Tommy was primarily a drummer while Jimmy played guitar. They were originally part of a band called The Times Showband before they started their own journey as The Swarbriggs. Despite parting ways musically in the 1980s, the Swarbriggs left a lasting legacy in the world of Irish music. They are still remembered for their energetic performances and catchy tunes.
sumy: Their most successful song was "That's What Friends Are For", which secured a third-place finish for Ireland in the 1975 Eurovision Song Contest.

base_text: Cnidaria is a classification of aquatic organisms, primarily marine, which includes species like jellyfish, sea anemones, corals, and hydras. This group is quite diverse, consisting of over 10,000 species worldwide. A defining feature of cnidarians is their specialized cells known as cnidocytes, which they use mainly for capturing prey. These cells contain organelles called nematocysts that can release a stinging substance. Furthermore, cnidarians exhibit two basic body forms: polyp and medusa. Polyps are generally sessile or stationary, while medusae are free-swimming. The life cycle of these creatures typically involves alternating between these two forms. Cnidarians have simple bodies with a single opening, the mouth, surrounded by tentacles. They are also known for their remarkable regenerative ability, being capable of regrowing parts of their body if damaged or lost. Despite their simplicity, cnidarians play vital roles in aquatic ecosystems, acting as predators and also serving as habitat for other species.
sumy: Cnidaria is a classification of aquatic organisms, primarily marine, which includes species like jellyfish, sea anemones, corals, and hydras.

base_text: H.R. McMaster is a retired United States Army lieutenant general who also served as National Security Advisor under President Donald Trump from 2017 to 2018. He devoted over three decades of his life to the army, serving in various capacities including fighting in the Gulf War and commanding troops in Iraq. McMaster is widely respected for his intellect and military strategy. In academic circles, he is known for his Ph.D. dissertation at the University of North Carolina, which later became a bestselling book on military leadership and strategy titled ‘Dereliction of Duty’. The book criticizes U.S. leadership during the Vietnam War. In his tenure as National Security Advisor, he was instrumental in shaping the foreign policy of the Trump administration. However, disagreements with the President led to his removal. Post his retirement, McMaster has continued to influence public discourse through his writing and public speaking engagements on matters of national security. He currently serves as the Fouad and Michelle Ajami Senior Fellow at the Hoover Institution at Stanford University.
sumy: McMaster is a retired United States Army lieutenant general who also served as National Security Advisor under President Donald Trump from 2017 to 2018.

base_text: The University of New Mexico is a prominent public research university located in Albuquerque, New Mexico, USA. It was established in 1889 and is the state's flagship institution. This higher education facility is known for its extensive commitment to research and teaching. It offers a wide array of undergraduate, graduate, and professional degree programs across various fields. The fields range from arts and humanities, sciences, engineering, to professional programs like law and medicine. The University of New Mexico is particularly recognized for its medical and law programs. It is also home to New Mexico's only schools of law, medicine, pharmacy, and architecture. The university campus encompasses a blend of architectural styles and hosts several museums, libraries, and a performing arts center. The athletic teams, known as the Lobos, participate in the Mountain West Conference. There are also numerous clubs, societies, and organizations for students to get involved in, along with opportunities for study abroad and research.
sumy: It offers a wide array of undergraduate, graduate, and professional degree programs across various fields.

base_text: Uzbekistan at the 2012 Summer Olympics refers to the participation of athletes from Uzbekistan in the 2012 Summer Olympics, held in London, the capital of the United Kingdom. The event took place from July 27 to August 12, 2012. This was the country's fifth consecutive appearance in the Summer Olympics since its independence from the Soviet Union in 1991. The team consisted of 54 athletes who competed in 14 sports categories. The country didn't win any gold medal but succeeded in securing a single silver and three bronze medals. The silver medal was won by the boxer duo, Abbos Atoev and Adilbek Niyazymbetov. Bronze medals were won by Soslan Tigiev in wrestling and Elshod Rasulov and David Modosyan in boxing. Another remarkable performance was from Rishod Sobirov in Judo, who won a bronze medal. This performance placed Uzbekistan 79th in the overall medal standings. Despite not winning any gold, it was a significant experience for Uzbek participants, showcasing their talents on an international stage.
sumy: The country didn't win any gold medal but succeeded in securing a single silver and three bronze medals.

base_text: Picea martinezii is a term used in botany to categorize a particular species of spruce tree. The name is derived from the genus Picea, which includes up to 35 species of coniferous evergreen trees commonly known as spruces. Martinezii is the species indicator, named in honor of a specific individual, often the person who discovered or categorized the species. Picea martinezii is part of the Pinaceae family, a large group of coniferous trees and shrubs including over 200 species. This species, like most spruces, is characterized by its sharp, pointed leaves and its conical shape. It has a woody stem and thin bark. It's native to specific geographic regions and usually found in cold and temperate regions like high mountains. Picea martinezii like other spruces, produce cones that carry the tree's seed. It contributes to the ecosystem as a habitat for creatures and soil stabilization. The wood of this tree can be used in construction or furniture making.
sumy: Picea martinezii like other spruces, produce cones that carry the tree's seed.

base_text: Transgender is a term used to describe someone whose gender identity differs from the sex they were assigned at birth. It is not related to sexual orientation and can encompass a wide variety of experiences and identities. Some people might identify as male while others as female, and others might not identify exclusively as either. Some transgender people undergo medical procedures to change their physical appearance, but not all choose to or are able to do so. It's important to respect a transgender person's self-identified pronouns and names. This word often forms part of broader discussions about the spectrum of gender and the societal norms associated with it. Also, it's key to remember that being transgender might imply different life experiences for different individuals. Public understanding and acceptance of transgender individuals have massively grown in recent years, yet they still face a significant amount of discrimination and misunderstanding. Everyone should strive to be informed allies, working to understand and respect transgender people's experiences and rights.
sumy: Transgender is a term used to describe someone whose gender identity differs from the sex they were assigned at birth.

base_text: Phil Mackenzie is a former professional international Canadian rugby union player. He was born on July 23, 1986, in Canada. He played as a wing in rugby, which is a position usually assigned to the fastest player on the team. Mackenzie started his professional career with Canada's national team, the Canada Wolverines, in 2008. He then moved to the UK, where he played for the Esher Rugby Football Club and later the Sale Sharks. He also played for London Welsh and San Diego Breakers. Internationally, he represented Canada in the Rugby World Cups in 2011 and 2015. After his playing career, Mackenzie turned to coaching and joined the Toronto Arrows for their 2019 inaugural season. Known for his speed and agility on the field, he has greatly contributed to the sport in Canada. Now, he is known as a prominent figure in Canadian rugby history.
sumy: Phil Mackenzie is a former professional international Canadian rugby union player.

base_text: The Handover of Hong Kong refers to the transfer of sovereignty over Hong Kong from the United Kingdom to the People's Republic of China. This historical event took place on July 1, 1997, marking the end of British colonial rule that had lasted for 156 years. Hong Kong had been a colony of the British Empire since 1842, following the First Opium War. The decision for the handover was formalized in the 1984 Sino-British Joint Declaration, and it was agreed that Hong Kong would become a Special Administrative Region of China. After the handover, Hong Kong was to maintain its capitalist economic system and partially democratic political system for 50 years under the principle of "one country, two systems". The transition has brought up concerns about the preservation of rights, freedoms, and autonomy in Hong Kong. Since the handover, Hong Kong has operated under the Basic Law, which serves as its constitution. However, tensions have risen over recent years between Hong Kong and Mainland China due to perceived encroachments on Hong Kong's freedoms. The handover also impacted the city's identity, with residents torn between a history of colonial influence and a future under Chinese rule. The Handover of Hong Kong is seen as a significant event in post-colonial history and continues to shape Hong Kong’s relationship with Mainland China.
sumy: This historical event took place on July 1, 1997, marking the end of British colonial rule that had lasted for 156 years.

base_text: Sigalegale is a cultural heritage originating from the Batak Toba tribe in North Sumatra, Indonesia. In Batak language, Sigalegale translates to puppet doll. These wooden puppets are typically life-size and unusually realistic, constructed in the likeness of humans. A Sigalegale doll is manipulatable and can be moved to simulate human-like movements, usually through a string mechanism attached to its joints. Sigalegale dolls are used in a traditional ceremonial dance called the Sigalegale Dance, performed during the funeral rites of someone who died without having any descendants. The doll, when animated by the puppeteer, is believed to host the spirit of the deceased person. The dance performance tells a story of war and death, symbolic of the soul's departure to the afterlife. Sigalegale has become an iconic tradition that is an integral part of the Batak Toba culture. Though less frequently seen in present day, such performances continue to hold considerable cultural significance. Sigalegale has also become an attraction for tourists that visit the region.
sumy: Sigalegale is a cultural heritage originating from the Batak Toba tribe in North Sumatra, Indonesia.

base_text: The 1979 Indianapolis 500 was an annual motor race held on May 27, 1979, at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway in Speedway, Indiana. It was the signature event of the 1979 Championship Auto Racing Teams (CART) series. A significant race as it marked the start of the "First open-wheel split" – where the United States Auto Club (USAC) split from CART. Rick Mears, driving for team Penske, emerged as the winner. It was Mears’ first Indy 500 win, in just his second year competing. There were several controversies related to safety regulations and kit specifications that year. The race was surrounded by both legal and political disputes, creating tensions amongst drivers and officials. The effect of these tensions led to a major change in the organizing of American Championship Car Racing. The 1979 Indianapolis 500 also marked the first time the race was telecast live flag-to-flag on network television in the USA. The broadcasting rights were held by ABC Sports.
sumy: Rick Mears, driving for team Penske, emerged as the winner.

base_text:
The head of a walrus is a crucial part of this majestic sea creature and plays a significant role in its survival in its arctic habitat. Walruses are readily identifiable because of their heads, featuring large tusks, deep-set eyes, a bulbous snout filled with whiskers, and two small round ears. The tusks are essential for survival and signify maturity and strength, used for fighting, dominance disputes, and breaking ice. It is part of the skull and grows throughout a walrus's life. 

The whiskers, also called vibrissae, help them locate their food in the deep, dark arctic waters. They are excellent sensors and can detect shellfish, a primary food source, on the ocean floor. The head's muscular structure helps to manipulate and excavate food. Furthermore, the eyes are well-adapted to see both above and under water. Lastly, their skull, including the head, is quite thick and robust to withstand the rigors of their environment. Essentially, the head of a walrus is perfectly designed for its harsh, marine environment.
sumy: Walruses are readily identifiable because of their heads, featuring large tusks, deep-set eyes, a bulbous snout filled with whiskers, and two small round ears.

base_text:
Veneto is a northeastern region of Italy, known for being one of the country's wealthiest and most industrialized areas. It covers an expanse of approximately 18,399 square kilometers and has a population of about five million people. The region is famed for its rich history, and its capital is Venice, renowned for its unique waterways and architecture.

The region comprises of seven provinces which include Belluno, Padua, Rovigo, Treviso, Venice, Verona, and Vicenza. Veneto is also known for its diverse landscapes, from the Po River delta to the Dolomite Mountains. Besides, it boasts numerous historical sites and beautiful cities, such as Verona, the setting for Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet.

The economy of Veneto is heavily reliant on industries like textile, furniture, and wine production. The region is Italy's largest wine producer and is the origin of noteworthy wine varieties like Prosecco and Amarone. Finally, Veneto also has a vast cultural heritage with several Venetian dialect languages spoken in addition to Italian.
sumy: The region comprises of seven provinces which include Belluno, Padua, Rovigo, Treviso, Venice, Verona, and Vicenza.

base_text: ZTE is a global telecommunications equipment and systems company headquartered in Shenzhen, China. Founded in 1985, it is one of China's leading telecom equipment manufacturers. The name ZTE stands for Zhongxing Telecommunication Equipment. The company is one of the world's leading developers of hardware and infrastructure software to support communications by voice, data, signaling, and video. ZTE's products are sold under different names worldwide. In addition to telecommunications equipment, ZTE is also known for its high-quality smartphones and consumer electronics. ZTE has faced controversy over allegations of spying and has had dealings with countries like Iran and North Korea, leading to sanctions by the U.S. Still, ZTE remains a vital player in the global telecommunications industry. Its ambitions and drive to innovate keep it at the forefront of telecommunication and information technology. ZTE is considered as a key competitor to Huawei, another major Chinese telecom equipment manufacturer.
sumy: ZTE is a global telecommunications equipment and systems company headquartered in Shenzhen, China.

base_text: Toxocara canis is a large parasitic roundworm that lives in the intestines of dogs. The adult worms produce eggs that are shed in the dog's feces. These eggs can then be ingested by other animals or humans through contaminated soil or food. When the eggs are swallowed, they hatch into larvae that travel through the body causing illness. This infection, known as toxocariasis, can lead to a range of symptoms, with severe cases impacting the lungs, liver, or central nervous system. Humans, particularly children, can become infected if they accidently ingest dirt or dog feces that contain the eggs. Puppies can be infected from their mother's milk. Regular worming of dogs and cleaning up their feces can help to prevent the spread of this parasite. Toxocara canis is a public health concern due to its potential to cause serious illness in humans. It is found worldwide, in every type of environment, but is more common in areas with high dog populations.
sumy: Toxocara canis is a large parasitic roundworm that lives in the intestines of dogs.

base_text: Pestil is a term that is commonly used to refer to a highly contagious and virulent epidemic disease that causes a high degree of mortality or death. The term is often associated with diseases that spread rapidly and widely throughout populations, leaving devastation in their wake. Most famously, the term is used to describe the Bubonic Plague, or 'Black Death', which decimated the population of Europe in the middle ages. The plague was caused by the bacterium Yersinia pestis, carried by fleas on rats, which then infected humans. Pestil can also refer to any disease that poses a serious threat to public health and social stability, causing widespread fear and panic. It is not limited to any specific disease but is rather a general term for any large-scale public health disaster. In addition to this, the term Pestil can also metaphorically refer to anything seen as morally corrupting or destructive. Despite the advances of modern medicine, the threat of a new Pestil is a continual concern. Understanding and combating these diseases is a key focus of epidemiology and public health.
sumy: The term is often associated with diseases that spread rapidly and widely throughout populations, leaving devastation in their wake.

base_text: Sarpatta Parambarai is a Tamil term that translates to 'the lineage of Sarpatta'. It is prominently known as the title of a 2021 Indian Tamil-language sports drama film. The title signifies a tradition of boxers, where Sarpatta refers to a clan or a faction of boxers competing in street or underground boxing matches in the Madras presidency during the mid 1970s. The term Parambarai adds more meaning, indicating a lineage or generations of boxers coming from the same clan or community. The key aspect of Sarpatta Parambarai is that boxing is not just a sport, but a way of life and a means of upholding honor and pride. The movie portrays the rivalry between different boxing clans, highlighting the struggle, grit, and determination of a young boxer from the Sarpatta Parambarai. The term itself encapsulates the story's essence, depicting the struggles and triumph of the protagonist while upholding a rich boxing tradition.
sumy: It is prominently known as the title of a 2021 Indian Tamil-language sports drama film.

base_text: Shane T. McCoy is a U.S. military officer. He is not only known for his service, but also for his work as a photographer. In his role as a military photographer, he has documented significant historical events. One of the most notable contributions of Shane T. McCoy is his photographic coverage of Guantanamo Bay detainees. These images became widely shared, providing a visual perspective on what was happening there. His work has been instrumental in bringing acutely debated issues to the forefront of public awareness. In the process, the photographer has raised crucial conversations about human rights and treatment of prisoners. Despite his contribution to journalism and photojournalism, his name often brings with it discussions about controversy and censorship in the U.S. Besides, McCoy’s images have both pushed for transparency and ignited debate on the ethical implications of his work.
sumy: These images became widely shared, providing a visual perspective on what was happening there.

base_text: USP6, also known as Ubiquitin Specific Peptidase 6, is a term used in biology. It refers to one kind of protease enzyme that is involved in the process of regulating the levels of proteins within cells. The role of USP6 is to detach the ubiquitin molecule from proteins. This step is essential because ubiquitin signals for proteins to be broken down in the cell. However, removing ubiquitin can halt protein degradation, which is what USP6 specializes in. Too much or too little activity of USP6 can lead to diseases, including tumorigenesis, particularly in the context of ubiquitin-related processes. USP6 is also known for causing benign tumors of the bone and soft tissue, which are known as aneurysmal bone cysts. Therefore, it can be seen as a pivotal enzyme in maintaining cell health and balance, despite having potential illness-causing abilities if not correctly managed.
sumy: USP6, also known as Ubiquitin Specific Peptidase 6, is a term used in biology.

base_text: The Lambertseter Line is a part of the Oslo Metro system, which is the primary transit service in the capital of Norway. This line specifically runs between the stations of Ryen and Bergkrystallen, in the suburban neighborhood of Lambertseter. The Lambertseter Line, also known as Line 4, was opened in 1957, making it one of the earlier lines in the system. It was the first metro line in Oslo to be operated by T-bane trains instead of trams. The line operates at a high frequency, with trains every 15 minutes throughout most of the day. The Lambertseter Line merges with the Østensjø Line at Ryen, and continues to the city center, resulting in a very comprehensive transit service. The line is completely underground, providing a quick and uninterrupted commute. It serves eight metro stations, which are all located in the southern part of the city. The Lambertseter Line allows residents in the Lambertseter area to easily access other parts of Oslo. This line plays a crucial role in Oslo's public transportation network.
sumy: It was the first metro line in Oslo to be operated by T-bane trains instead of trams.

base_text: Wood is a natural material derived from trees and other woody plants. It has been used for thousands of years for both fuel and as a construction material for buildings, furniture, tools, boats and more. It is organic, meaning it comes from plants and is composed of carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen. Wood is mainly made up of cellulose, hemicellulose, and lignin. These substances give wood its strength and adaptability, and their proportional combination also attributes to differences in hardness among various wood types. The color, grain pattern and hardness of wood depend on the species of the tree it comes from. Wood can be either hardwood or softwood, depending on the tree from which it's sourced. It can be cut and shaped using tools, polished, and coated with paint or varnish. It also plays a crucial role in ecosystems as it's a habitat for many organisms and serves as a carbon sink. However, overexploitation of wood can lead to deforestation, threatening biodiversity and contributing to climate change.
sumy: Wood is a natural material derived from trees and other woody plants.

base_text: Rodion Oslyabya is a notable figure in Russian history, especially remembered for his participation in the Battle of Kulikovo. He was a medieval Russian monk who was also known as a warrior during the 14th century. Renowned for his physical strength and piety, he is often depicted in Russia's historical and religious literature. His primary claim to fame is his participation in the Battle of Kulikovo in 1380, where Russian principalities united to face the Mongols. He is famously depicted in the epic poem, "The Tale of the Battle of Kulikovo," where he is portrayed as a peacemaker. Despite being a monk, he was known to have taken up arms in this crucial battle. Though he died in this battle, he was posthumously elevated to a heroic status. For many, he symbolizes the perfect blend of spiritual and physical virtue, symbolizing Russia's religious devotion and martial courage. His name is often invoked as a symbol of Russian valor and Orthodoxy. Today, his image can be found in many churches in Russia as a religious icon.
sumy: His primary claim to fame is his participation in the Battle of Kulikovo in 1380, where Russian principalities united to face the Mongols.

base_text: The Nicaraguan Socialist Party, also known as Partido Socialista Nicaragüense (PSN) in Spanish, is a political party in Nicaragua. The PSN was founded in the early 1940s, making it one of the oldest political organizations in the country. This political party adheres to the ideology of socialism. This means that they promote social ownership and democratic control of the production's means. During the 1980s, the party was reportedly involved in various anti-Sandinista activities, despite being a left-wing party. However, the party has undergone numerous transformations and splits since its foundation. Today, it is a minor party with limited influence on Nicaraguan politics. Over the years, the PSN has typically allied with other leftist parties for general elections. The party is committed to fighting for social justice, labor rights, and the national independence of Nicaragua. It has remained active in Nicaragua's political scene, albeit with less significance than in past decades.
sumy: This political party adheres to the ideology of socialism.

base_text: Koparkhairane railway station is a train station located in the city of Navi Mumbai, in the Indian state of Maharashtra. Part of the Mumbai Suburban Railway network, the station falls on the Harbour Line, which is one of the three main line routes of this network. The station primarily caters to the residential and commercial areas of Koparkhairane. It has fast and slow locals, with trains running from both the platforms. The station is well connected and acts as a significant mode of transportation for the local residents. Besides, it also lies close to Thane-Belapur road providing easy access to private transportation when needed. It is managed by the Central Railway division of Indian Railways. Simplifying commuting, the station sees frequent trains to key locations such as CST and Panvel. A ticket counter, public transport connectivity and small eateries nearby add to the convenience of commuters. Overall, Koparkhairane railway station is an essential node in the city's public transportation system.
sumy: Simplifying commuting, the station sees frequent trains to key locations such as CST and Panvel.

base_text: An electric strike is a kind of electronically operated lock often used in door security systems. The strike allows for doors to be locked or unlocked remotely using an electric current. It works in conjunction with a mechanical latch or lockset. When no power is supplied to the strike, it will stay in a locked position, preventing the latch from moving. However, when power is supplied, the strike will move into an unlocked position, allowing the latch to retract and the door to open. This operation can either be fail-secure or fail-safe, which dictates the strike's position during a power failure. Fail-secure models remain locked when power is lost, whereas fail-safe models unlock. Electric strikes are popular in high-security settings like offices and commercial buildings. They can be controlled by several methods, including keypads and wireless remote controls. They offer a balance of security and convenience, simplifying access control.
sumy: An electric strike is a kind of electronically operated lock often used in door security systems.

base_text: California State Route 103, often referred to as SR 103, is a state highway in the U.S. state of California. It is located in the Los Angeles area, more specifically in Los Angeles County. The entirety of this highway is known as Terminal Island Freeway. SR 103 is relatively short, measuring just 1.4 miles in length. It serves as a connector between Terminal Island and Long Beach with a broader highway network. The highway begins at the intersection with SR 1 (Pacific Coast Highway) and ends at the junction with SR 47 near the Vincent Thomas Bridge. Despite its size, it is crucial for regional transportation as it plays a significant role in freight movement from the Port of Los Angeles. The California Legislature defined Route 103 in 1964. However, as of 2021, there are plans to remove it, and convert the area into a local street due to environmental issues. Hence, SR 103 might not exist in the future.
sumy: The entirety of this highway is known as Terminal Island Freeway.

base_text: "Porgy and Bess" is an opera that was first performed in 1935. It was created by the American composer George Gershwin, who is renowned for his contributions to both classical music and jazz. The story of "Porgy and Bess" is based on the novel "Porgy" by DuBose Heyward, who also collaborated with Gershwin on the opera's libretto. The opera is set in the African American community of Catfish Row in Charleston, South Carolina. Its narrative revolves around the lives and struggles of its titular characters: Porgy, a disabled beggar, and Bess, a woman with a disreputable past trying to escape it. Known for its dramatic intensity, "Porgy and Bess" is a tragic love story meshing elements of community, discrimination, and resilience. It is also notable for its memorable music, which includes the well-known arias "Summertime" and "I Got Plenty o' Nuttin'". Over the decades, the opera has been subjected to varying interpretations and controversies, particularly pertaining to racial representation. Despite this, it is seen today as a significant piece of American cultural history. The opera continues to be performed worldwide and is recognized as one of Gershwin's greatest works.
sumy: It was created by the American composer George Gershwin, who is renowned for his contributions to both classical music and jazz.

base_text: The Norwegian National Road 41 is a notable highway in Norway. It runs from E18 in the region of Akland, through the country's southern inland region, and to the E39 highway at Knapstad. The entire road measures about 420-kilometers long, making it one of the longest roads in the country. This national road was opened for public use in 2010 and crosses three counties namely Agder, Vestfold og Telemark, and Viken. Its route links various towns and regions including Risør, Arendal, Evje, Kristiansand, Hægeland, and Drangedal to mention a few. The National Road 41 goes through some important tourist destinations as well, such as the Mineral Park in Evje and Hornnes. Because of its extensive length and connectivity, it serves as an important circulation venue for vehicular traffic, goods, and people. It is maintained by the Norwegian Public Roads Administration. It's also regularly upgraded and extended to accommodate growing vehicular traffic and improve mobility across regions. Despite its length, most parts of this road are two-lane undivided.
sumy: The Norwegian National Road 41 is a notable highway in Norway.

base_text: Marymoor Park is a 640-acre public park located in Redmond, Washington. This park is the biggest in King County's park system, drawing over 3 million visitors annually. It's maintained and operated by King County's Department of Natural Resources and Parks. The Park features vast recreational areas, including soccer fields, a climbing rock, a baseball field, and tennis courts. It also boasts a large concert venue that hosts a variety of music performances each year.  For nature lovers, it flaunts an off-leash dog area, a community garden, and a birdloop trail. The Clise Mansion, a historic landmark, is also housed in the park. The Sammamish River also flows through the park, offering opportunities for water activities. It also supports sustainable practices with facilities like a composting and recycling center. Marymoor Park hence can be viewed as a hub of outdoor activities, eco-friendly practices and cultural events.
sumy: The Park features vast recreational areas, including soccer fields, a climbing rock, a baseball field, and tennis courts.

base_text: Waste minimisation refers to the process and activities that aim to reduce the amount of waste produced and its impact on the environment. It involves efforts taken at all stages of production and consumption to decrease the quantity of waste. This process includes reducing, reusing, recycling and composting waste materials to decrease their volume going to landfill. It can be practiced by both individuals and companies, and is often a major part of environmental management systems. Methods include using less packaging, substituting materials, improving process efficiency, and recycling waste back into the production process. Waste minimisation is an important factor in the sustainable use of resources. It not only helps to conserve the natural environment, but can also lead to cost savings and efficiencies. The aim is to stop waste from being created in the first place. Solid waste management contributes significantly in this effort. Society must strive to consume less and become more efficient for waste minimisation to be successful.
sumy: It can be practiced by both individuals and companies, and is often a major part of environmental management systems.

base_text: The 2007 Senegalese Senate election refers to the voting process that occurred in Senegal to determine the members of the country's Senate (upper house of Parliament). The second Senate election in the country's history, took place on 19th August 2007. Local councillors and National Assembly deputies made up the electoral college that voted in these elections, not the general public. Out of a total of 100 seats, 35 were directly elected and 65 were appointed by the President. The Sopi Coalition, which was the ruling party led by then president Abdoulaye Wade, won majority of the seats. This particular election was marred by controversy. Opposition parties called for a boycott of the Senate elections, citing that it was costly and unnecessary burden on the country's economy. There were also allegations of bribery and corruption. Despite criticism and boycotts, the elections went on as planned. As a result of this election, the balance of power in the Senate moved heavily in favor of the ruling party.
sumy: Local councillors and National Assembly deputies made up the electoral college that voted in these elections, not the general public.

base_text: 0 Avenue is a street name that marks the international boundary between Canada and the United States, particularly in the Western part of both countries. It's specifically located between British Columbia in Canada and Washington State in the U.S. This road runs parallel to the 49th parallel, which is the agreed boundary line between the two nations. 0 Avenue stretches across various municipalities in Canada such as Surrey and Abbotsford. Despite being a road that one could drive on, it's essentially a border line with border markers and patrols. It's an interesting geographic feature that both separates and connects the two nations. For travelers, certain parts of the road are subject to checks by border security forces. The term '0 Avenue' may sometimes create confusion as it implies a beginning of some sort, but it's simply a name that signifies its location as a border road. It's a place where you can see the cooperation, regulation and co-existence between two nations in a tangible way. Despite its unique location, for the residents around, it's just a part of their normal, everyday landscape.
sumy: It's an interesting geographic feature that both separates and connects the two nations.

base_text: The Eleventh Doctor is a character from the globally renowned British TV series, Doctor Who. This role is the eleventh incarnation of the protagonist, the Doctor, who is a time-traveling alien known as a Time Lord from the planet Gallifrey. Matt Smith, a British actor, portrayed the Eleventh Doctor from 2010 to 2013. This particular character is known for his youthful appearance and eccentric, yet compassionate personality. From his iconic bow tie to his tweed jacket, the Eleventh Doctor is remembered for his unique style. This character travels through time and space in a ship known as the TARDIS, frequently with companions who aid in battling various enemies. The Eleventh Doctor's companions primarily included Amy Pond, Rory Williams, and Clara Oswald. Just like all the incarnations of the Doctor, the Eleventh Doctor faces unique challenges and adventures, contributing to the continued growth and change of the character over the series. The Eleventh Doctor sacrificed his life to save a town called Christmas and was then regenerated into the Twelfth Doctor. Overall, the Eleventh Doctor holds a significant place within the Doctor Who series, marking a new era of the show after its revival.
sumy: Matt Smith, a British actor, portrayed the Eleventh Doctor from 2010 to 2013.

base_text: HPTi, an abbreviation for High Performance Technologies, Inc, is a company specializing in technological solutions and services. Founded in 1991, it provides cutting-edge technology in areas such as cybersecurity, data analytics, and cloud computing. HPTi's primary clients are in the public sector, with a major focus on U.S. federal government agencies. Their solutions are designed to help clients meet their goals in an efficient and effective manner. They undertake projects ranging from system modernization to developing custom software applications. The HPTi team comprises of highly skilled engineers and analysts. Notably, HPTi has a reputation for providing high levels of customer service and for implementing innovative problem-solving strategies. In 2012, HPTi was acquired by DRC, an Alion Science and Technology company. Despite the acquired, the company continues to innovate in its field. Overall, HPTi is known for its commitment to delivering high-quality technology solutions and services.
sumy: HPTi, an abbreviation for High Performance Technologies, Inc, is a company specializing in technological solutions and services.

base_text: The Mark 14 nuclear bomb is a type of thermonuclear weapon that was developed by the United States during the 1950s. This device was part of the Mark series of nuclear weapons, a line of bombs created during the Cold War. The Mark 14 is significantly more powerful than earlier models as it uses a fusion-based design, allowing for a much larger explosion. It was designed with a sphere shape and a high yield of approximately 5 megatons. Its design also included a levitated pit, which would enhance its performance. However, it had a short lifespan; it was taken into service in 1954 but by 1955 it was retired due to its high weight and large size which made it impractical for use with bombers of the era. Today, the Mark 14 stands as an interesting case study in the history of nuclear weapons, encapsulating both the technological advancements and logistical challenges associated with such devices. It's also a reminder of the kind of devastating firepower nations were willing to develop and possess during the tense years of the Cold War.
sumy: The Mark 14 is significantly more powerful than earlier models as it uses a fusion-based design, allowing for a much larger explosion.

base_text: Storm Uru is a term commonly used to denote a cyclonic storm that South Pacific regions, like Fiji, experience. The term "Uru" is often given to these cyclones as part of the tradition of naming storms in the Pacific. This is reminiscent of how other storms across the world are named, often involving unique local or regional aspects. The severity of a storm like Storm Uru can vary, ranging from category one to category five, with five being the most severe. These storms are associated with high-speed winds and heavy rainfall, often causing significant damage in their path. The effects of Uru can cause disruptions in the form of floods, loss of crops, or destruction of property. This can lead to displacement of people and a need for disaster management. Moreover, such storms often pose a risk to marine life as well. The naming system helps accurately track and communicate about specific storms, aiding public safety. The World Meteorological Organization maintains the rotating lists of names in order to streamline the process.
sumy: This is reminiscent of how other storms across the world are named, often involving unique local or regional aspects.

base_text: The term Columbus Bus Station refers to a transport hub located in Columbus, the capital city of the U.S. state of Ohio. This facility is mainly dedicated to providing bus services to the local population and visitors. It is a pivotal point for interstate, regional, and local bus transport systems. The Columbus Bus Station facilitates the movement of people to and from different locations. Various companies run their bus services from this station, the most notable one being Greyhound, a nationally recognized transport provider. Services from this station cover diverse routes, touching various cities and towns. The facility not only provides transport services but also has amenities like waiting rooms, restrooms, ticketing services, and eateries for riders' convenience. Security measures are also in place to ensure the safety of commuters. It forms an integral part of the city's overall transport structure.
