Born in Kyiv, Ukraine, Kholodenko trained at the Moscow P.I. Tchaikovsky Conservatory. His remarkable talent has been recognized with several awards, apart from the Cliburn. Aside from his solo performances, Kholodenko has performed with many prominent orchestras and at prestigious concert venues worldwide. His repertoire spans a broad range of classical pieces from various periods. Kholodenko is also known for recording works by various composers, further showcasing his versatility and virtuosity. However, his fame was marred by a personal tragedy in 2016 - his two daughters were found dead in Texas and his estranged wife was charged with their murder. The incident received extensive media attention but Kholodenko continues his musical career, creating a pool of majestic classical music, and inspiring a new generation of pianists.
sumy: Vadym Kholodenko is a renowned Ukrainian pianist who shot to global fame after winning the Fourteenth Van Cliburn International Piano Competition in 2013.

base_text: "The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel" is a British comedy-drama film directed by John Madden. The movie, released in 2012, follows a group of British retirees who decide to spice up their lives by leaving their homeland and moving to India. They choose to stay at a seemingly luxurious retirement home, the eponymous Best Exotic Marigold Hotel. However, upon their arrival, they discover that the hotel is not as sophisticated as its advertisements claimed. Although the hotel is outdated and neglected, the story unfolds with the retirees deciding to stay. The film explores themes of cultural clash, age, and love, with the group navigating through their new adventure in an exotic land. The movie boasts a star-studded cast including Judi Dench, Bill Nighy, and Maggie Smith. "The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel" has been highly acclaimed for its humor, heart, and the performances of its lead actors. Furthermore, it spawned a successful sequel in 2015, "The Second Best Exotic Marigold Hotel". Its combination of strong performances, humor and emotional depth has made it a favorite among audiences.
sumy: "The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel" is a British comedy-drama film directed by John Madden.

base_text: The culture of Nigeria is a broad term that encompasses the traditions, beliefs, and customs of its diverse ethnic groups. Being the most populous African nation, Nigeria is home to approximately 250 ethnic groups, each contributing a unique blend of cultural expression. The food, music, literature, art, and religion of Nigeria represent an intertwining of indigenous practices and outside influences, including those from Arab, European and American cultures. Nigeria is renowned for its vibrant music scene which includes genres like Afrobeats and highlife, as well as for its film industry, known as Nollywood. The Nigerian literary scene boasts many widely acclaimed authors like Wole Soyinka and Chinua Achebe. Traditional Nigerian art ranges from Nok terracottas to Yoruba masks and Benin's famous bronzes. Nigeria is also known for its traditional festivals and masquerade events showcasing unique music, dance, and costumes. Nigerian traditional clothing often includes brightly colored materials, body art, and hairstyles. The culture is also influenced by indigenous and colonial religions such as Christianity, Islam, and traditional African religions. Overall, Nigeria's culture is a lively, thriving, and dynamic mixture of indigenous and global influences.
sumy: Being the most populous African nation, Nigeria is home to approximately 250 ethnic groups, each contributing a unique blend of cultural expression.

base_text: The 2019 Cork North-Central by-election was a special election held in Ireland on November 29, 2019, to fill a vacant parliamentary seat in the Dáil Éireann, the country's lower house of parliament. This vacancy was created when the sitting deputy (member of parliament), Billy Kelleher, was elected to the European Parliament in May 2019. According to Irish law, his seat in the Dáil was required to be filled. The by-election took place in the Cork North-Central constituency, which is one of Ireland's forty constituencies and located in the county of Cork. Padraig O'Sullivan of the Fianna Fáil party won the by-election, and took up the vacant seat. This election was regarded important because it was seen as a major test of political sentiment ahead of a general election, expected in 2020. The vote was also pivotal for the Irish parties seeking to shape their strategies. It was one of four simultaneous by-elections, but each constituency was held independently with separate ballots. The results were indicative of the political landscapes at the time and the election served as a platform for parties to gain political leverage before the anticipated general election.
sumy: The 2019 Cork North-Central by-election was a special election held in Ireland on November 29, 2019, to fill a vacant parliamentary seat in the Dáil Éireann, the country's lower house of parliament.

base_text: Michael Attwell was an established English actor and illustrator, recognized for his diverse contributions to the entertainment industry. He was born in London in 1943 and passed away in 2006. His acting career spanned several decades, with him appearing in numerous TV shows, films, and theatre. Audiences might remember him for his roles in popular British television shows like 'Doctor Who,' and 'EastEnders.' In recent years, Attwell was known for playing Kenny Beale in 'EastEnders.' However, his talent was not limited to acting: he was also a noteworthy illustrator who drew for children's books. Attwell worked on more than 800 publications as an illustrator, often bringing children's stories to life with his whimsical style. Renowned for his versatility and commitment, Michael Attwell left an indelible mark both on screen and on the page. His love for his craft was widely acknowledged in the entertainment world. Despite his passing, his works continue to entertain and inspire.
sumy: Michael Attwell was an established English actor and illustrator, recognized for his diverse contributions to the entertainment industry.

base_text: William Letwin is a noteworthy individual most recognized for his contributions to the field of political science. He was born in 1922 and rose to prominence as an economist and legal philosopher. He is most known for his work at the London School of Economics, where his studies largely focused on the history of economic thought. Letwin was also a renowned author, writing extensively on topics like economic liberalism and the philosophy of law. His most famous book, "The Origins of Scientific Economics," is a widely studied piece in the intellectual history of economics. Letwin belonged to a well-educated family with his wife also being a scholar, featured in the political and intellectual domain. His two children, Oliver and Laura, both enjoyed successful careers in politics and journalism, respectively. Despite his death in 2013, William Letwin's philosophical theories continue to inform and influence a broad range of academic discourse. His legacy remains embedded in the fabric of political science academics, demonstrating his indelible impact on the field. Thus, William Letwin is an eminent figure in the realms of economics, law, and social theory.
sumy: William Letwin is a noteworthy individual most recognized for his contributions to the field of political science.

base_text: Earthsiege 2 is a mecha-style, single-player, vehicular combat game, developed by Dynamix and released in 1996. It is the sequel to the original Earthsiege game and part of the larger Starsiege universe, a science fiction franchise including video games and other related media. In Earthsiege 2, the Earth is at war with a race of sentient machines, known as Cybrids. The players operate large robots, known as Hercs, to fight these adversaries. This game is renowned for an immersive storyline and its complex control system that emulates the controls of a real robot. It includes over 40 missions, offering battles around the globe, including Arctic, urban, and desert settings. Earthsiege 2 features an AI teammate system that allows players to give orders to their team members for more strategic gameplay. It also allows for customization of the Hercs, enabling different weapon and shield configurations. Despite its age, Earthsiege 2 is still played and appreciated for its simulation elements and challenging gameplay. It's often considered as one of the defining games in the mech genre.
sumy: In Earthsiege 2, the Earth is at war with a race of sentient machines, known as Cybrids.

base_text: Seidou Njimoluh Njoya is a notable figure in Cameroonian history, being the 18th King, or Sultan, of the Bamoun people, one of the country's major tribal groups. His reign began in 1992 following the death of his father, Sultan Ibrahim Mbombo Njoya. Seidou Njimoluh Njoya, like his predecessors, played a significant role as a traditional ruler within the political landscape of Cameroon. Besides his kingly duties, Njoya is also an agricultural enthusiast who promotes farming and has initiated several agricultural projects in his kingdom. His reign has not been without controversy, but he has also had notable achievements, including the promotion of inter-tribal peace and cultural preservation within his kingdom. Despite the socio-political changes in Cameroon, Seidou Njimoluh Njoya remains a respected leader and figure of authority revered by the Bamoun people. His leadership blends traditional values and modern governance principles. An aspect of Njoya's rule has been his efforts towards educational development within his kingdom. Overall, Seidou Njimoluh Njoya represents the continuity of the Bamoun monarchy's influence on Cameroon's cultural and political life.
sumy: Besides his kingly duties, Njoya is also an agricultural enthusiast who promotes farming and has initiated several agricultural projects in his kingdom.

base_text: Erin McLeod is a Canadian professional soccer player who primarily operates as a goalkeeper. She was born on February 26, 1983, in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. McLeod is recognized internationally for her contributions to the Canadian national team, with whom she has amassed over 100 appearances. She played in the Women's World Cup multiple times and was part of the Canadian team that won bronze at the 2012 London Olympics. McLeod also grew her career in various professional leagues, including the Women's Professional Soccer in the United States and Damallsvenskan in Sweden. She is known for her outstanding athleticism, skill, and leadership on and off the pitch. Apart from her soccer career, McLeod is also an accomplished artist and motivational speaker. She is an ambassador for mental health awareness and openly discusses her personal struggles to inspire others. Moreover, McLeod is a vocal advocate for LGBTQ+ rights, being openly gay herself. Through her achievements and dedication, Erin McLeod has become a significant figure in the world of women's soccer.
sumy: McLeod is recognized internationally for her contributions to the Canadian national team, with whom she has amassed over 100 appearances.

base_text: The 1983 Italian Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race that marked the 13th round of the 1983 FIA Formula One World Championship. It took place at the Autodromo Nazionale Monza, in Italy, on September 11, 1983. This annual racing event is considered to be part of the highest class of single-seat auto racing sanctioned by the Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile (FIA). The 1983 Italian Grand Prix was won by Nelson Piquet, a Brazilian racing driver who drove for the Brabham team. Second and third places were taken by René Arnoux and Patrick Tambay, both from the Ferrari team. This race particularly stood out due to various technical failures and issues encountered by the drivers. These incidents significantly impacted the final results, making the race unpredictable and tense. The 1983 Italian Grand Prix is remembered today for its high drama and unexpected turn of events. Despite these dramatic moments, it was an integral part of the Grand Prix circuit and contributed significantly to the thrilling nature of the 1983 World Championship. The race has since been etched in sporting history as a remarkable event in Formula One racing.
sumy: It took place at the Autodromo Nazionale Monza, in Italy, on September 11, 1983.

base_text: The geology of Puerto Rico encompasses the physical structure and composition of the island of Puerto Rico and the processes that have shaped it over time. This Caribbean island is predominantly composed of volcanic and plutonic rocks, limestone, and alluvial deposits, reflecting its volcanic and oceanic origin. Its geological systems have been shaped by tectonic processes at the boundary of the Caribbean and North American plates, where the island was formed through volcanic and tectonic activity. The island's central mountain range, Cordillera Central, is a direct result of these geological processes. The terrain also includes karst topography in the north, characterized by caves, sinkholes, and caverns in limestone regions. The southeast region is dominated by semiarid conditions and less fertile volcanic soils. Puerto Rico has an active seismic history, experiencing both minor earthquakes and significant seismic events. It's also underlain by numerous groundwater aquifers, some of which are used for drinking water. The geology of the island is significant for understanding its biodiversity, natural resources, and potential natural hazards. Climate, including the impact of tropical storms and hurricanes, directly affects and is in turn influenced by the geology of Puerto Rico.
sumy: The southeast region is dominated by semiarid conditions and less fertile volcanic soils.

base_text: Han van Meegeren was a Dutch artist and art forger, considered one of the most ingenious art forgers of the 20th century. Born in 1889 in the Netherlands, he initially gained notoriety as a talented portrait artist. However, criticism of his original work led him to forge paintings of famous artists, notably Johannes Vermeer. Van Meegeren developed a unique technique to mimic the appearance of centuries-old paint. He fooled experts with his forgeries, making millions in the process, which were sold to museums and private collectors. His most famous forgery is "Christ at Emmaus," sold as a Vermeer. However, he was discovered during World War II when it was thought he'd sold a Dutch national treasure to the Nazis. To avoid treason charges, he confessed to the forgeries. Despite his illegal activities, many admire his technical skills and audacity. Van Meegeren died in 1947, his life demonstrating a complex mixture of ingenuity, greed, and, ironically, artistic talent.
sumy: Van Meegeren developed a unique technique to mimic the appearance of centuries-old paint.

base_text: "Gridman the Hyper Agent" is a live-action Japanese series which originally aired in the 1990s. It was produced by Tsuburaya Productions, known for their popular "Ultraman" series. The story revolves around three young children who discover they can create their own virtual world using a computer program. However, the villain Khan Digifier manages to infiltrate that world with the intent to cause destruction. The protagonist of the series is a digital being named Gridman who resides within the computer system. Gridman has the ability to merge with a young boy named Naoto to fight the monsters that Khan Digifier creates in the virtual world. Distinctly, Gridman fights these battles within the computer system, not in the physical world. The series combined both elements of traditional live action series as well as Computer-Generated Imagery. The show was later adapted into an American series named "Superhuman Samurai Syber-Squad". Recently, it was rebooted as an anime series titled "SSSS.Gridman" by Studio Trigger.
sumy: It was produced by Tsuburaya Productions, known for their popular "Ultraman" series.

base_text: Floyd Sneed is a Canadian drummer who was born in 1942. As a musician, he is most famously recognized for his association with the American rock band, Three Dog Night. The band, active from 1968 until 1976, produced a number of top hits, and Sneed was a significant contributor to their success as their drummer. He was adept at a variety of percussion instruments, and his consistent rhythm was a key element of the band's sound. Even after the disbandment of Three Dog Night, Sneed continued his musical journey with other bands and solo musicians. Apart from music, Sneed was also involved in the field of arts, notably painting, and his work is recognized in several art circles. Floyd Sneed's exceptional contribution to music has granted him a prominent place in the history of rock and roll music. Despite being born in Canada, he has significantly influenced American rock music of his era. He is a multi-talented personality known for his unique style of drumming. His work continues to influence and inspire future generations of musicians.
sumy: As a musician, he is most famously recognized for his association with the American rock band, Three Dog Night.

base_text: Wolfmother is an Australian rock band that originally formed in 2000. The founding members were Andrew Stockdale (vocals and guitar), Chris Ross (bass and keyboards), and Myles Heskett (drums). The band is known for its unique and dynamic blend of hard rock, psychedelic rock, and heavy metal. Influences of 1970's rock bands like Led Zeppelin and Black Sabbath can be identified in their music. When their self-titled debut album was released in 2005, it was a big commercial success, even earning them a Grammy. Over the years, Wolfmother has faced multiple line-up changes, with Stockdale being the only constant member. Despite many changes, the band has continued to produce music and tour around the world. Wolfmother's music has been featured in films, video games, and advertisements. The name of the band, Wolfmother, signifies strength, independency and wild spirit. But, the story behind the band's name is not clear and appears to be a name that the band members simply liked.
sumy: Wolfmother is an Australian rock band that originally formed in 2000.

base_text: J. D. Rymbai is a name of a political figure in India. He belongs to the Indian National Congress party. His full name is Jospin Dymbai Rymbai and he was born on the 7th of June, 1950. He served as a legislator in his state Meghalaya and was also the chief minister therein during 2005 to 2006. His political career started as a member of the legislative assembly in the Nongbah-Wahiajer Constituency, representing it four times. Rymbai is well regarded as a senior leader within his party. Despite facing political challenges during his administration, he held various significant positions within the government. He passed away on the 24th of January, 2007, leaving a substantial impact on Indian politics, particularly within his home state Meghalaya. His life has remained an example for many upcoming political figures.
sumy: His full name is Jospin Dymbai Rymbai and he was born on the 7th of June, 1950.

base_text: The term 'Hadean zircon' refers to tiny crystal fragments of the mineral zircon that were formed during the Hadean eon, the first geological eon of Earth that began around 4.6 billion years ago. These zircons are considered the oldest pieces of the Earth's crust and are primarily found in Western Australia's Jack Hills region. They provide valuable insights into the conditions that existed on Earth shortly after its formation. Despite their small size, these zircons have proven so durable that they have survived countless geological processes over billions of years. The Hadean zircons are significant because their chemical composition can reveal data about the early Earth's atmosphere, crust, and the presence of water. They have been critical to the understanding of the Earth's early history, including theories that the planet may have been cool enough for water, and possibly life, to exist earlier than previously thought. The study of these tiny, yet significant crystals completely challenges previous beliefs regarding the Hadean eon's harsh and inhospitable conditions. Therefore, Hadean zircons are an invaluable resource in the study of Earth's geological past.
sumy: These zircons are considered the oldest pieces of the Earth's crust and are primarily found in Western Australia's Jack Hills region.

base_text: Erwin Obermair is not a term, but a name of a person. He is an Austrian jurist who has contributed a lot to the development of corporate and business laws in Austria. Erwin Obermair was born in 1945 in Linz, Austria. After finishing his law studies and earning a PhD in Law from the University of Vienna, he began his career as an attorney. A significant part of his work involves research and teaching, particularly in the areas of corporate, business and tax law. He taught at the Johannes Kepler University in Linz, where he became the head of Institute for Business and Tax Law. He also contributed to the amendment of Austrian Commercial Code and has authored several books on business and corporate laws. Obermair served as the head of the Commercial Law section of the Vienna Bar Association. His work and contributions in the field of commercial law have been recognized nationally and internationally. Today, Obermair is known as one of the most influential figures in Austrian juristic circles.
sumy: He is an Austrian jurist who has contributed a lot to the development of corporate and business laws in Austria.

base_text: Malt is a product obtained from barley and other grains through a process known as malting. Initially, these grains are soaked in water then allowed to germinate. During germination, the grains produce enzymes which breaks down the grains' starches into sugars. The germination process is then halted by drying the grains in a kiln. Consequently, the end product known as malt is obtained which is rich in enzymes and sugars. Malt is typically used in brewing beer, distilling spirits, and in the production of malt vinegar. When used in brewing, the malt sugars are consumed by yeast to produce alcohol and carbon dioxide. Beside beverages, malt is also used in baking and the production of malted milk candies. The flavor of malt is characterized as slightly sweet and toasty. In summary, malt is a versatile product central to brewing, distilling and even baking industries.
sumy: When used in brewing, the malt sugars are consumed by yeast to produce alcohol and carbon dioxide.

base_text: Saint Seiya is a popular Japanese manga and anime series created by Masami Kurumada. The storyline focuses on mystical warriors called 'Saints' who are champions of hope. These Saints have the ability to channel the power of the Cosmos. This power allows them to wear protective cloths and fight against evils that threaten the world. The title character, Seiya, is a Saint who bears the Bronze Cloth of Pegasus. The series primarily revolves around Seiya and his fellow Bronze Saints as they protect the goddess Athena from various threats. Since its inception in 1986, Saint Seiya has been adapted into an animated series, movies, spin-off manga and anime series, and merchandise. The series also emphasizes themes of friendship, sacrifice, and valor. Over time, Saint Seiya has gained significant fan following worldwide. Its complex character relationships and high action scenes have contributed to its enduring success.
sumy: Saint Seiya is a popular Japanese manga and anime series created by Masami Kurumada.

base_text: Pectinivalva acmenae is a species of moth falling under the family Nepticulidae. It is largely distributed across Australia. This species has a specific link to the Acmena plant, which is part of the Myrtaceae family, implying that it has likely evolved through interactions with these plants. The adult moths of this species are quite minuscule, petal-like in structure, and have a wingspan around 8.1-9.5 mm. The color of the adults varies but is typically brown. They tend to lay eggs on the leaves of their host plants which subsequently serves as a food source for the larvae. The caterpillars create a gall in the leaves of the host plant in which they live and consume. As a part of the Nepticulidae family, Pectinivalva acmenae is just one example of the highly specialized ecological roles that these "micro-moths" play. This species is scientifically identified and named by Dutch entomologist, Kees den Nijs, who did extensive studies on the taxonomy of the group. Further studies are needed to understand the full biological and ecological roles of the Pectinivalva acmenae.
sumy: Pectinivalva acmenae is a species of moth falling under the family Nepticulidae.

base_text: The War of the Golden Stool, also known as the Yaa Asantewaa War, refers to a military conflict that took place in 1900. This war happened in West Africa, between the British Imperial forces and the Asante Empire, modern day Ghana. The main cause of the conflict was a golden stool, which was seen as the symbol of Asante sovereignty and identity. When the British colonial Governor, Sir Frederick Hodgson, demanded to sit on the Golden Stool, he offended the Asante people deeply. The stool was sacred and even the Asante king was not allowed to sit on it. The request sparked a rebellion, led by the queen mother of the Asante, Yaa Asantewaa. The Asante fought fiercely to protect their stool and their sovereignty. This war was one of the last major wars on the continent of Africa to be led by a woman. The British eventually managed to suppress the rebellion, but never captured the Golden Stool. The war demonstrated the Asante resistance against British colonialism and their determination to protect their cultural heritage.
sumy: This war happened in West Africa, between the British Imperial forces and the Asante Empire, modern day Ghana.

base_text: The Watergate scandal was a major political scandal that occurred in the United States during the early 1970s. It stemmed from a break-in at the Democratic National Committee (DNC) headquarters at the Watergate office complex in Washington, D.C. The Nixon Administration tried to cover up involvement in the break-in. It led to the discovery of multiple abuses of power by the Nixon administration, including the existence of a secret White House group known as the "Plumbers". Other practices like 'dirty tricks', bugging the offices of political opponents and people of whom Nixon or his officials were suspicious became known. After a series of revelations through investigative journalism, public opinion began to turn against President Nixon. This scandal eventually led to the resignation of Richard Nixon, the then-president of the United States, on August 8, 1974. His resignation marked the first time in American history that a sitting president chose to leave office. His successor, Gerald Ford, would later pardon Nixon for any crimes he may have committed while in office. Watergate scandal remains as a significant moment in American political history, representing a breach in the public's trust in government.
sumy: After a series of revelations through investigative journalism, public opinion began to turn against President Nixon.

base_text: Quinton de Kock is a South African professional cricketer and one of the leading figures of South Africa's national cricket team. He was born on December 17, 1992, in Gauteng, South Africa. He is known for being a left-handed batsman and also for his role as a wicketkeeper, a dual role that few in cricket can effectively fulfill. De Kock made his debut in international cricket in 2012, playing against New Zealand. Since then, he has built a reputation as one of the most efficient wicketkeepers and aggressive opening batsmen in the cricket world. He is especially renowned for his fast scoring ability in one-day cricket matches. Quinton de Kock holds several records, including the fastest century by a South African in One Day Internationals (ODI). Apart from the national team, he also represents several cricket franchises in domestic and international cricket leagues. He is often compared to former South African wicketkeeper-batsman, Mark Boucher. Off the pitch, de Kock is also known to be a man of few words and prefers to let his cricket do the talking.
sumy: He is especially renowned for his fast scoring ability in one-day cricket matches.

base_text: Telecom Egypt is the primary telecommunications company in Egypt, which has both historical and economic importance. The company provides telephone, internet, data, and other technology-related services to customers in Egypt, and it has a long history dating back to 1854, which makes it the oldest telecom operator in the Middle East and Africa. It operates a vast network of landlines in the country and is also the only landline service provider in Egypt. Telecom Egypt also owns and operates six submarine cable systems. In addition to its domestic services, Telecom Egypt also provides international voice and data services on its networks for other telecom operators. The company's operations are expansive, but it's primarily stable due to the strong demand for telecom services in Egypt. In 2017, Telecom Egypt entered the mobile market, thus becoming a full-fledged integrated operator. It remains a vital part of Egypt's telecom industry, helping to advance the sector within the country and globally. It is listed on both the Egyptian Stock Exchange and London Stock Exchange. Telecom Egypt also participates in social responsibility programs as part of its activities, going beyond merely providing telecom services.
sumy: The company provides telephone, internet, data, and other technology-related services to customers in Egypt, and it has a long history dating back to 1854, which makes it the oldest telecom operator in the Middle East and Africa.

base_text: A ventifact is a natural rock formation that results from the process of erosion caused by wind carrying small particles, like sand. The particles act like sandpaper on the rock surface, gradually changing its shape and texture. The wind direction determines the shape of the ventifact, as it erodes the side of the rock facing the wind more intensely. As such, most ventifacts have a sculpted, often faceted appearance. They can be found in various desolate windblown landscapes with plenty of loose particles, such as deserts or tundras. Depending on the size and shape of the particles, and the wind speed, a ventifact can take anywhere from a few years to several millennia to form. The term 'ventifact' is derived from Latin, with 'ventus' meaning 'wind' and 'factum' meaning 'made'. Despite their natural occurrence, these formations provide important insight into past wind patterns and climate conditions, making them a fascinating feature in the world of geology.
sumy: As such, most ventifacts have a sculpted, often faceted appearance.

base_text: Doc Powers is a term that refers to Michael Riley Powers, who was an American professional baseball player in the early 1900s. He was a physician, which is why he was often called "Doc" Powers. He played in Major League Baseball as a catcher for three teams throughout his career which included the Louisville Colonels, New York Yankees (then known as the Highlanders), and the Philadelphia Athletics. He was born on April 22, 1870, in Pittsfield, Massachusetts. His career in Major League Baseball spanned nine years, from 1898 till 1909. Doc Powers was known for his physical endurance and stamina. Unfortunately, his career and life were cut short due to complications from surgeries following an injury sustained in a baseball game. He died on April 26, 1909, just four days after his 39th birthday. Despite his career being cut short, Doc Powers is remembered in the history of American sports. His story also brought attention to the risks involved in playing professional baseball.
sumy: Unfortunately, his career and life were cut short due to complications from surgeries following an injury sustained in a baseball game.

base_text: Nassella is a term used to refer to a specific genus of perennial bunching plants in the grass family, known scientifically as Poaceae. This genus is primarily native to the Americas, with the majority of species found in Argentina, Mexico, and the United States. Nassella includes various species of needlegrasses, some of which are important for land management and soil erosion control. These grasses are adapted to various conditions like dry climates, high altitudes and can survive even in poor soil. However, some species of Nassella, like Nassella tenuissima, are considered invasive outside of their native range. These grasses have slender, elongated spikes that resemble needles, hence the common name 'needlegrasses'. Nassella plants are also known for their aesthetic appeal and are often used in landscaping for their ornamental value. Nevertheless, they can become problematic for agriculture if not properly managed. Despite this, in their native habitats, Nassella grasses are an important food source for wildlife. Thus, Nassella is highly valued both for its environmental role and visual appeal.
sumy: These grasses are adapted to various conditions like dry climates, high altitudes and can survive even in poor soil.

base_text: The Andrew McNally House is a historical property located in Altadena, California. It was designed by Frederick Roehrig, a prominent architect, and built for Andrew McNally, a renowned map publisher, in 1887. The house features a Queen Anne Style architecture, which was prevalent during the era. The mansion is set on a piece of land that measures approximately three acres. It has been preserved and displays a grandeur that is reflective of the period it was built in. One of its unique features is an aviary, built to house exotic birds. Also, the home has a stunning sun room which was originally a conservatory for plants. In 2012, it was designated a historical landmark by the state of California. The Andrew McNally House retains most of its original characteristics and continues to be a representation of 19th-century elegance in the modern day. It stands as a landmark to remember McNally's contributions to the publishing industry.
sumy: The mansion is set on a piece of land that measures approximately three acres.

base_text: The French battleship Lorraine was a maritime combat vessel that served in both World War I and World War II. This ship was part of France's Bretagne-class battleships, a group of warships built in the early 20th century. Commissioned in 1916, Lorraine was built by the French shipyard, Arsenal de Brest. She was designed to combat the increasing threat of German naval power during World War I. In World War II, Lorraine played a crucial role in the Free French Naval Forces after France's surrender to Germany. Her notable deployments include operations in the Mediterranean and the North African campaign. After the war, in the late 1940s, Lorraine was decommissioned from active service and later repurposed as a school ship. She was eventually scrapped in 1953. The Lorraine was thus a key asset to the French Navy during two pivotal global conflicts. The ship's legacy lies in her service during these wars and her contribution to the strength of the French naval force.
sumy: The French battleship Lorraine was a maritime combat vessel that served in both World War I and World War II.

base_text: The Billung March refers to a territory located in the northeastern regions of modern-day Germany. Dating back to the 10th century, this area was governed by the Billung family under the rule of Herman, who was a leading vassal of Otto I. The Billung March was not a traditional "march" or borderland along the outer borders of the Ottonian Empire, however, it was named as one due to its function in the defense against Slavs. The region functioned almost as an independent principality within the larger Holy Roman Empire. It included parts of modern Saxony, Mecklenburg, and territories up to the Oder River. The Billung March played a pivotal role in Germany's medieval history and the defense of the German realm against Slavic invasions. Over time, the territories under the control of the Billung family fragmented. The end of the Billung rule came in the 12th century. Afterwards, the territory was passed to the Duke of Saxony. To date, its historical significance is acknowledged by historians.
sumy: Dating back to the 10th century, this area was governed by the Billung family under the rule of Herman, who was a leading vassal of Otto I.

base_text: "We Are Making a New World" typically refers to a strive for a radical change or transformation in the current state of affairs, or a vision to bring forth a better future or a new reality. It can imply changes at different levels such as societal, environmental, technological, or even individual. The phrase suggests a collective effort, involving multiple people, communities, or nations, working in tandem to create this transformation. It's often used in context of building sustainable environments, evolving technologies, or reshaping societal norms. It symbolizes hope, evolution and progress, and the aspiration to create a more inclusive, evolved and harmonious world. Its interpretation can vary depending on its usage, but it inherently expresses a forward-thinking perspective and vision.
sumy: It can imply changes at different levels such as societal, environmental, technological, or even individual.

base_text: Containerart refers to an art form that employs the use of shipping containers or similar reusable elements as a medium. These structures are often seen in urban spaces, acting as temporary installations for events or permanent structures providing innovative solutions for living and working spaces. Containerart challenges traditional architectural norms, pushing for sustainable and green design. The mobility of these containers makes them ideal for artists wanting to showcase their work on an international stage. Containerart can take many forms, from murals painted on the side of the container to structures entirely built out of these units. Artists may choose to preserve the industrial aesthetic or transform it completely. Besides visual appeals, Containerart also often communicates themes of globalization, displacement, and sustainability. Essentially, it embodies the intersection of art, design, and architecture in a unique and contemporary manner. Unlike the traditional gallery space, Containerart provides a more immersive and sometimes interactive experience for the viewer. Overall, it’s a fascinating approach to creating art and space out of utilitarian objects.
sumy: Containerart refers to an art form that employs the use of shipping containers or similar reusable elements as a medium.

base_text: "Kiss Me Once" is a phrase often used to express a desire or request for a single act of affection, specifically a kiss. It carries an emotional weight, usually linked to romance or sentimental significance. The phrase can be a part of dialogue in a romantic scene, song, or novel, symbolizing an intense moment between two characters. Its usage conveys a sense of longing, passion, or closeness. While "Kiss Me Once" is often associated with a romantic context, it can also be a phrase of close friendship or familial affection. "Kiss Me Once" is also the title of a popular album by Kylie Minogue. While the phrase is usually a request, it sometimes infers a goodbye. Here, the essence is not the act of kissing, but the emotion behind it. Thus, "Kiss Me Once" is a powerful phrase, evoking longing, affection, and sometimes, sorrow.
sumy: It carries an emotional weight, usually linked to romance or sentimental significance.

base_text: A hangover is a group of unpleasant signs and symptoms that can develop after drinking too much alcohol. These may involve physical discomfort such as headache, nausea, fatigue, dehydration, a feeling of weakness, and sensitivity to light and sound. It might also include psychological problems like poor memory, difficulty concentrating, and mood disturbances like irritability or depression. The severity of hangover symptoms can vary depending on how much alcohol was consumed and the person's individual response. Hangovers begin after blood alcohol levels start to fall sharply, which is usually the next morning after a night of drinking. Unfortunately, they can last up to 24 hours. Drinking alcohol causes a urine output increase, leading to dehydration, often indicated by thirst, dizziness, and lightheadedness. Other factors contributing to hangover symptoms include disturbed sleep patterns, direct effects of alcohol on the brain, and possibly other chemicals found in alcoholic beverages. There's no sure cure for a hangover other than time and rehydration.
sumy: Drinking alcohol causes a urine output increase, leading to dehydration, often indicated by thirst, dizziness, and lightheadedness.

base_text: Henry John Walter was an influential British figure. He was born into an aristocratic family in 1812 and over time, he established a significant place in society. He climbed the social ladder partly because of his family's position and partly because of his own abilities and achievements. He had a prolific career in various areas including politics, business, and philanthropy. In 1832, he was elected to the British House of Commons as a member of Parliament. In addition to his political pursuits, he was also a successful businessman, involved in numerous industries and sectors. Furthermore, he made a name for himself through philanthropy, championing the advancement of education and health. Notably, Walter was the founder and builder of Bear Wood, a grand mansion where he and his family resided. Walter ultimately left a lasting legacy in Britain, with his impact enduring past his death in 1889. His life reflects the far-reaching influence of a well-rounded, driven individual from the Victorian period.
sumy: He climbed the social ladder partly because of his family's position and partly because of his own abilities and achievements.

base_text: Gary Player is a renowned professional golfer from South Africa. Born on November 1, 1935, he has won around 165 professional tournaments throughout his six-decade career. Player is one of the most successful golfers in history and he is noted for his excellent fitness regime. He is internationally recognized as a 'World Golf Hall of Famer'. Player is one of five golfers to have achieved a Grand Slam, winning all four of golf's major championships in his career. These tournaments include the Masters Tournament, U.S. Open, The Open Championship, and the PGA Championship. Player turned his passion for golf into a global enterprise, establishing Gary Player Design, a golf course design company. He is also known for his humanitarian work through The Player Foundation. Gary Player, with his distinct style of play, dedication to the game, and extensive charity work, remains an iconic figure in the world of golf.
sumy: Born on November 1, 1935, he has won around 165 professional tournaments throughout his six-decade career.

base_text: The Western Defense Command (WDC) was a formation of the United States Army during World War II. Its primary responsibility was the defense of the West Coast of the United States. Established in 1941, the command was part of the U.S. defensive plan against possible attacks from the Axis powers. The WDC was created by consolidating existing units in the western U.S. Its commander was General John L. DeWitt. During the war, the WDC was involved in a variety of defensive measures, including coastal surveillance and anti-aircraft operations. Most infamously, the WDC was responsible for the internment of Japanese-Americans on the West Coast. After the end of World War II, the WDC was disbanded. Today, its duties are principally carried out by the U.S. Northern Command.
sumy: The WDC was created by consolidating existing units in the western U.S. Its commander was General John L. DeWitt.

base_text: Michael Chance is a notable figure in the world of classical music. He is an English countertenor having gained esteemed reputation for his powerful and emotive voice. Chance was born in March 1955, and his passion for music led him to study at King's College in Cambridge. His musical specialty lies in baroque, where he interprets early music with a unique style and sensitivity. Chance's discography is extensive, reflecting a successful career that spans several decades. His talent has taken him around the globe, performing in operas, concerts, and recitals. Additionally, he is a frequent collaborator in orchestral and ensemble projects. Michael Chance has been a professor of singing at the Royal College of Music, passing on his knowledge to a new generation of musicians. Furthermore, he is the founder of the Grange Festival, an annual operatic event held in Hampshire. Thus, Michael Chance is a multi-talented artist, his influence extends beyond just his performances but also to the realms of teaching and event organization.
sumy: He is an English countertenor having gained esteemed reputation for his powerful and emotive voice.

base_text: The Tyrrell 026 is a model of Formula One race car, which was designed by the Tyrrell Racing organization. The organization was established by Ken Tyrrell, a renowned figure in motor racing. The Tyrrell 026 was used in the 1998 Formula One season, a series of high-speed, single-seater races. The car was driven by Toranosuke Takagi and Ricardo Rosset, two experienced race car drivers. The car was designed with a Ford Zetec-R 3.0 V10 engine, which provided considerable power. Though it was a complex and advanced machine, it struggled with reliability and didn't show high-performance levels during the season. Unfortunately, this model did not secure any points in the championship. The Tyrrell 026 was the last car from Tyrrell Racing, as the organization was sold to British American Racing at the end of the season. Despite the challenges, the Tyrrell 026 holds a significant place in motor-racing history as the closing chapter of Tyrrell's foray into Formula One racing.
sumy: The organization was established by Ken Tyrrell, a renowned figure in motor racing.

base_text: Valdivia is a city and commune in southern Chile, located in the province of the same name. It is the capital of the Los Ríos Region in Chile. Its name comes from Pedro de Valdivia, a Spanish conquistador and the first colonial governor of Chile. The city is known for its picturesque setting along the Calle-Calle River, just before it meets the Pacific Ocean. In addition to this, Valdivia is also the cultural, administrative, and economic hub of the region. Historically, it's also notable for being the site of one of the most powerful earthquakes ever recorded, which hit the city in 1960. Valdivia is also famous for its university, Universidad Austral de Chile, which contributes to its vibrant student culture. The city is also characterized by its German influenced culture and architecture, a legacy of 19th century immigration. Today, Valdivia is a popular tourist destination due to its unique combination of natural beauty, historical significance, and cultural attractions. So, in essence, Valdivia is a historical, cultural and natural landmark of Chile.
sumy: Its name comes from Pedro de Valdivia, a Spanish conquistador and the first colonial governor of Chile.

base_text: The Chrysler Atlantic is concept car that was unveiled by Chrysler Corporation in 1995. This vehicle was a two-door, four-seat, luxury coupe, and was considered a stylistic masterpiece by some. Its design inspiration was drawn from the famous 'Bugatti Atlantic 57SC' of the 1930s. The Atlantic was one of the few old-style designs of the 1990s and was a rear wheel drive car modeled with the classical proportions of a long hood and short rear. The Atlantic’s lavish design was penned by Chrysler's in-house stylist Bob Hubbach. While many believed it would go into production, that never happened, remaining only a prototype to showcase the design prowess of Chrysler. The car had an inline eight-cylinder engine, which was unconventional at its time. The engine sophistication added to the high performance and elite reputation of the vehicle. Even though the Atlantic never made it to production, it remains an iconic symbol of Chrysler’s willingness to experiment with design during the 1990s.
sumy: The Atlantic’s lavish design was penned by Chrysler's in-house stylist Bob Hubbach.

base_text: Inanna is one of the most significant deities from ancient Mesopotamia and was worshiped primarily within the Sumerian civilization. Known as the goddess of love, beauty, sex, and war, her character was complex and multifaceted. The early Sumerian texts establish Inanna as the daughter of the moon god Nanna and sister to the sun god Utu. She is also associated with the planet Venus, the morning and evening star in the sky. With many temples and shrines dedicated to her worship, she was one of the most venerated deities of the Sumerian pantheon. Her most significant myths include her descent to the underworld and the sacred marriage with the shepherd god Dumuzid. The Epic of Gilgamesh, an ancient Mesopotamian text, recounts several stories featuring Inanna. She was later equated with the Akkadian goddess Ishtar, and many of her attributes carried over to Greek and Roman goddesses like Aphrodite and Venus. Inanna's symbolic representation as both a life giver and a destroyer embodies the duality of feminine power in ancient religious mythology. Her cult declined along with the Sumerian civilization but her influence can still be seen in modern culture and spirituality.
sumy: With many temples and shrines dedicated to her worship, she was one of the most venerated deities of the Sumerian pantheon.

base_text: Johannes Belsheim was a notable Norwegian academic and theologian from the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Born in 1829, he made significant contributions to theological studies and biblical translations. Belsheim is best known for his works in Latin and Greek languages, and his expertise in old manuscripts. He dedicated much of his life to translating ancient texts into the Norwegian language, to make them more accessible. He also worked diligently on a collection of texts not included in the traditional Bible, known as apocryphal literature. His scholarly contributions led to his appointment as a University Scholar at the renowned University of Christiana (now known as University of Oslo). Despite facing some academic controversies, his legacy remains impactful in the world of religious studies and ancient languages. Belsheim passed away in 1909, but his work continues to be referenced and studied by contemporary researchers and theologians. In his lifetime, he made a significant mark in the field of theology and language, expanding the reach of ancient text translations. His contributions to biblical texts were immeasurable and continue to influence theological studies to this day.
sumy: Born in 1829, he made significant contributions to theological studies and biblical translations.

base_text: Stressed out is a commonly used term to describe a feeling of extreme mental or emotional tension. It is often the result of prolonged periods of high stress which can be caused by various life situations such as work pressures, relationship issues, or financial problems. When a person is stressed out, they may experience symptoms like anxiety, fatigue, irritability, or mood swings. The prolonged feeling of being stressed out can also have serious impact on one's physical health, leading to issues such as headaches, insomnia, and even heart disease. People may also start to feel overwhelmed, unable to think clearly or make decisions. Ultimately, feeling stressed out is a signal from our body and mind that we need to change something about our current situation or lifestyle. It indicates that some form of action is needed to manage or reduce the stress we are experiencing, be it through relaxation techniques, lifestyle changes, or seeking professional help. However, it's important to remember that some degree of stress is normal in life and can sometimes play a positive role in motivation and performance.
sumy: When a person is stressed out, they may experience symptoms like anxiety, fatigue, irritability, or mood swings.

base_text: The term 'Ludi' is based on ancient Roman culture, where it broadly signifies 'games'. The Roman Ludi were public games or spectacles which were presented in honor of the Roman gods. These were usually sponsored by leading Romans or the imperial court. Ludi aimed at appeasing the gods and entertaining the public, and they included chariot races, theatrical performances, and gladiatorial combats. Prominently, Ludi Romani or Roman Games, and Ludi Plebeii or Plebeian Games, were held annually. These Ludi were an integral part of Roman culture, contributing to the city's communal identity and sense of unity. These games, in some cases, also served a political purpose as emperors often used them to boost their popularity among the populace. Though these games emphasized fun and entertainment, they were also marked by displays of excessive violence and brutality, especially in the gladiatorial contests. Nevertheless, Ludi significantly defined social, religious, and political aspects of the Roman Empire. Today, remnants of the Ludi culture are evident in various modern sporting events and festive occasions.
sumy: These games, in some cases, also served a political purpose as emperors often used them to boost their popularity among the populace.

base_text: The 2014 FA Cup final refers to the concluding match of the Football Association Challenge Cup (FA Cup) that took place in 2014. The FA Cup is an annual knockout football competition, one of the oldest football tournaments in British history. In 2014, Arsenal and Hull City were the two teams competing in the final. The game took place on 17th May 2014 at the Wembley Stadium in London, England. Hull City quickly led the match 2-0 within the first eight minutes. However, Arsenal managed to come back, ending the match in a 3-2 victory after extra time. This victory marked Arsenal's 11th win in FA Cup history. The game is considered highly memorable because of Arsenal's comeback from a two-goal deficit. This match was of great significance for Arsenal, marking an end to their 9-year trophyless period. Their last major trophy win had been the FA Cup in 2005.
sumy: However, Arsenal managed to come back, ending the match in a 3-2 victory after extra time.

base_text: A sound post is an integral component of stringed instruments like the violin, viola, cello, and double bass. It is a small, cylindrical piece of wood that is wedged inside the instrument, aiding in sound projection. The sound post sits vertically inside the instrument, typically positioned beneath the treble end of the bridge, connecting the front and back plates of the instrument. Positioned correctly, the sound post transmits the vibrations from the strings to the body of the instrument, enhancing the sound quality. Incorrect placement might lead to less-than-satisfactory sound production or potential damage to the instrument. The sound post's position can be adjusted to fine-tune the instrument's tonal qualities. The term "sound post" is also used to refer to the soul of the instrument, mostly because of how crucial it is for the sound. Without the sound post, the instrument would sound hollow and would lack the resonance that we associate with these types of stringed instruments. In the event of a fall, the sound post can potentially shake loose, necessitating expert repositioning. The sound post may appear simple, but it is vital for the instrument's overall sound and functionality.
sumy: A sound post is an integral component of stringed instruments like the violin, viola, cello, and double bass.

base_text: Glenn Kimber is not a term but rather a prominent figure known for his work in the field of education. He is an American educator and the founder of Thomas Jefferson Education, a teaching methodology focusing on leadership and responsibility. Glenn Kimber also serves as the head of the Kimber Academy. He also collaborates with his wife, Julianne Kimber, to develop educational curriculum. Besides, he is the author of several educational texts and resources. Glenn Kimber's distinctly innovative approach to education and teaching has significantly contributed to the field. His strong advocacy for student-led, hands-on learning has made a significant impact and transformed numerous lives in the process.
sumy: He also collaborates with his wife, Julianne Kimber, to develop educational curriculum.

base_text: Don Kolloway is not a term but rather a person who was popularly known in the field of baseball. base_text: Sundar Pichai is a prominent figure in the tech world, currently serving as the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Alphabet, the parent company of Google, since 2019. Born in India in 1972, he moved to the United States for further studies after obtaining his degree from the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur. He holds an M.S. from Stanford University and an MBA from Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania. He joined Google in 2004, where he led the development of Google Chrome and Chrome OS, which have been very successful initiatives. Pichai became the CEO of Google in 2015 after Google's restructuring into Alphabet Inc. His leadership role expanded to include all of Alphabet's subsidiaries, including Google, in 2019. Pichai is recognized worldwide for his leadership and innovation. His ability to strategize and implement has made him one of the key persons in the world of technology and digitization. He has shaped Google into a global leader in tech products and services. Under his leadership, both Google and Alphabet have pushed the boundaries of technology, achieving significant growth.
sumy: Born in India in 1972, he moved to the United States for further studies after obtaining his degree from the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur.

base_text: Vibration refers to a mechanical phenomenon where oscillations occur about an equilibrium point. It is a repeated back-and-forth or up-and-down motion which can be experienced in many physical systems. It can occur naturally, like in the case of seismic vibrations, or it can be made to occur artificially, such as by the vibrating motion in our cell phones. This oscillating nature of vibration involves potential and kinetic energy being constantly converted back and forth. The speed of the vibration is known as the frequency, measured in Hertz (Hz). The larger the vibration amplitude, the stronger the amount of energy being transferred. Vibration can be either undesirable, like in the shaking of a building during an earthquake, or desirable, for instance in musical instruments to produce sound. Vibration is generally a periodic process, meaning it repeats in cycles, and it is usually quantified by its amplitude and frequency. It is a core part of waves, both mechanical and electromagnetic, which carry energy from one location to another. In scientific terminology, the study of vibration is known as vibrology.
sumy: Vibration refers to a mechanical phenomenon where oscillations occur about an equilibrium point.

base_text: Sai Baba of Shirdi, also known as Shirdi Sai Baba, was an Indian spiritual leader who is considered by his followers to be a saint, a fakir, a sadguru, and an incarnation of God. He is revered by both his Hindu and Muslim followers. His teachings combine elements of Hinduism and Islam such as the importance of love, forgiveness, helping others, charity, contentment, and the pursuit of inner peace. Sai Baba lived in Shirdi, a small village in Maharashtra, India, throughout his life. His exact birth date is unknown, but his death was on October 15, 1918. After his death, his legacy has continued with devotees visiting his tomb in Shirdi. Sai Baba is also known for his miracles, making destructive situations into peaceful ones and healing the sick. He strongly discouraged the love for perishable things and encouraged the path of true spiritual practice and development. Today, his teaching and the messages he conveyed continue to inspire millions of people around the world. His life and teachings remain a significant tool for peace and harmony.
sumy: Sai Baba of Shirdi, also known as Shirdi Sai Baba, was an Indian spiritual leader who is considered by his followers to be a saint, a fakir, a sadguru, and an incarnation of God.

base_text: Cooper Black is a heavily weighted, old style serif typeface which was designed by Oswald Bruce Cooper in 1921. It is known for its bold and curved design that was largely popular during the 'roaring twenties.' Oswald Cooper designed some of the most famous advertising and display faces of the 20th century, with Cooper Black being his most popular. Cooper Black was originally produced by the Barnhart Brothers & Spindler type foundry before eventually being taken over by the American Type Founders (ATF). The font itself is widely recognizable for its rounded, inflated forms and thick, dense strokes, giving it a unique and playful character. It has been widely used in advertising, poster design, album covers and other forms of popular culture. People may know it as the typeface used in the logo for the hit television show Seinfeld, and in the Beach Boys' Pet Sounds album. Its popularity led to influence and inspirations to many other typeface designs. Despite its age, Cooper Black is still appreciated for its distinct features and continues to be used in various design projects. Its inherent heaviness makes it suitable for emphasizing particular text.
sumy: It is known for its bold and curved design that was largely popular during the 'roaring twenties.'

base_text: Arrenurus is a genus name used within the scientific classification of a diverse group of water mites. These are minute aquatic arthropods that belong to the family Arrenuridae. Spanning across several species, Arrenurus water mites are found in many freshwater habitats around the world. They inhabit water bodies including marshes, streams, lakes, and ponds. These mites are considered quite beneficial to their ecosystems. They play crucial roles in freshwater food webs and are important for nutrient cycling. Arrenurus mites are parasitic during their larval stage, commonly found on aquatic insects and can occasionally be found on tadpoles or small fish. Despite their small size and microscopic nature, they are quite significant to biological research and ecological studies. The lifecycle of Arrenurus includes egg, larva, protonymph, tritonymph and adult stages. Detailed study and identification frequently needs microscopic examination due to their small size.
sumy: Spanning across several species, Arrenurus water mites are found in many freshwater habitats around the world.

base_text: Roni Benise, whose real name is Roni Bejarano, is a celebrated American guitarist who is particularly known for his talent in Spanish guitar. His music style is a fusion of rock, world music, salsa, and flamenco. He is also known for the stunning theatrical stage shows he puts up which are complete with elaborate costumes, passion, and excitement.
